title: linguine
directions: Cook linguine as directed.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Mix Salad Supreme over linguine noodles.
Add tomatoes, olives, mushrooms, cucumbers and broccoli.
Add Zesty Italian dressing. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, combine 1 tablespoon oil, peppers and onion.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil and chicken to skillet; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add spices, seasoning, 1/4 cup water, lime juice and cilantro.
Stir until blended.
Return vegetables to skillet and heat thoroughly.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and let cool. Cut from bones in bite sized pieces.
Have ready the celery, onion and green pepper.
Saute in some of the chicken fat until tender, but not brown.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Then add tomato soup, mushroom soup, pimentos, olives, the chopped chicken and a little of the broth.
Let cook slowly while noodles are cooking. Cook noodles in the remaining chicken broth.
Add water if necessary.
When noodles are tender, add to the chicken mixture. Mix well and fold in cheese.
Put in casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: emerald salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan and let set. Cook remaining ingredients, except sour cream, until thick.
Fold in sour cream.
Spread mixture on top of jello.
Chill several hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt cheese, soup and margarine.
Stir in onion and rice. Pour over broccoli in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with meat tenderizer; cover with liquid smoke.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with foil.
Next day, sprinkle brisket with mixture of remaining ingredients.
(I put all remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix them thoroughly before putting on the brisket.) Cover tightly with foil; bake 2 hours at 300°.
Loosen foil; bake 5 hours at 200°.
Remove meat from pan; set aside 1 hour before slicing.
Strain any grease from pan juices (or chill in deep freezer for easy removal).
Slice brisket very thin across grain; serve with hot degreased liquid or barbecue sauce of your choice.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: ritz bits treats
directions: Spray a large roaster pan with cooking spray.
Combine Ritz Bits, nuts and pretzels in roaster pan.
Set aside.

title: turkey-cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions (until tender); drain.
Cook broccoli according to package directions until tender; drain.
Remove broccoli stems and dice, leaving florets whole.
Meanwhile in saucepan, melt butter, then stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and milk.
Stirring constantly, cook until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
In a greased shallow casserole or 8-inch small square baking pan, arrange noodles, broccoli stems and turkey.
Pour cheese sauce over top.
Arrange broccoli florets on top.
Bak 15 minutes.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Arrange bite size pieces of angel food cake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or container.
Combine instant pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake pieces.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries, breaking with fork.
Do not stir.
Spoon over pudding.

title: quick apple strudel
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Add a little more milk, if necessary.
Turn out onto floured board; knead gently for 2 minutes.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and brush with melted butter. Cover with apples; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Roll up like jelly roll; form into semi-circle on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While warm, frost with icing made of confectioners sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and a few drops of hot water.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Add salt, fruit, soda and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Then sprinkle brown sugar over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Ice cake while still hot.

title: salt clay
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Cook over low heat.

title: texas party dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve in crock-pot. Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except peanut butter cups.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake in ungreased mini muffin tins.
Remove from oven and press peanut butter cup into center and cool.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: polenta
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a heavy saucepan.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Gradually sprinkle in cornmeal, whisking constantly to prevent lumps from forming.
Gently boil 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often with a wooden spoon, until very thick, but still pourable.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/4 cup butter and cheese.
rinse a 15 1/2 X 10 1/2 inch jellyroll pan with cold water.
Do not dry pan.
Spread hot Polenta evenly in pan with a rubber spatula.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes or until firm.

title: garlic bread plus
directions: Slice bread.
Melt butter and add garlic to taste.
Spread on bread.
Mix onions, tomatoes, oregano and oil (may be done earlier).
Spread on top of garlic butter bread evenly and broil until bread is golden.
Serve immediately.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Serve with celery, carrot strips, broccoli, etc.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar on high speed for about 5 minutes. Turn to low.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 300° for 2 hours.

title: 8 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: coke icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well until smooth.
Add small amounts of hot water to thin, if necessary, for spreading consistency.

title: mexican chicken spaghettini
directions: Cook spaghetti 8-10 minutes to tender, drain.
Keep warm.

title: dutch babies
directions: While gathering ingredients, melt butter in 13 x 9-inch glass pan or 2 glass pie pans at 425°.
In a blender, mix the eggs, milk, flour and salt until smooth.
Pour egg mixture into melted butter slowly, to not crack hot plate or pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Serve with powdered sugar and lemon juice, syrups or yogurt.
Puffs up.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add sifted salt, flour and cocoa and blend well. Chill dough in refrigerator for about an hour.
Press and mold into two long smooth rolls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Roll in nuts, pressing in on all sides.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator overnight.
Using thin, sharp knife, cut in slices 1/8-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for about 10 minutes.
Cool, melt chocolate in double boiler and frost center of cookies.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Make 2 crust pie recipe. Put water, sugar and cream of tartar in a pan and bring to a boil. Add Ritz crackers and bring to a boil; boil 1 minute. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover with top pie crust. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Saute onion, jalapeno, garlic and stew meat in oil.
Add tomatoes, soups, water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add tortillas and cheese to soup. Continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Crush candy bars. Cover bottom of pie crust, then set aside the rest. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until soft and creamy. Add balance of candy bars, leaving enough to garnish top of pie. Refrigerate pie.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then cut in shortening.
Mix water and yeast until yeast dissolves.
Then gradually add this to dry ingredients, stirring with a fork until it crumbles.
Knead on floured surface until a smooth ball is formed.
Divide in half and let stand 10 minutes.
Roll each half about 1/8-inch thick; cut into 3 squares.
Fry in hot oil for about 30 seconds on each side.
Drain and serve with honey.

title: scones
directions: Put the flour and the salt into a bowl; make a well in the center.
Put in the egg and 1 cup milk.
Mix to a smooth batter. Add rest of milk and fruit.
Then melt butter or oil in heavy skillet.
Drop three pancakes into the hot fat and fry them on both sides to a golden brown.
Turn them when puffed and full of bubbles (as you do griddle cakes or scones).
Serve hot with sugar.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a large bowl. Add to mixture, eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, fill muffin pans 2/3 full; bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place the Monkey Pot on a pie pan to catch any excess drip.
Melt the butter in a small saucepan. Brush the interior of the mold well with the butter*.
Open refrigerator biscuits and dip the biscuits individually in the butter and layer them into the pot, taking care to see that each layer alternates over the last.
Bake for 15 minutes, then cover with foil and continue to bake for an additional 30 minutes or until done.
Tap the top; it will sound hollow when done.
Invert the mold onto a plate and serve piping hot.

title: great grammy's apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add cinnamon, lemon juice and water.
Mix sugar and flour; cut in butter to make crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in milk and beaten egg.
Mix again and add onion; mix again.
Batter comes out thin.
Fry in deep oil.

title: praline cheese cups
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
With a fork, remove a small amount of the center from each dessert cup. Fill centers of dessert cups with cream cheese mixture.
Arrange pecans atop each.
Chill until serving time.
Just before serving, heat together ice cream topping and brandy until warm.
Spoon atop filled dessert cups.
Makes 4 servings.

title: granola
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large baking pan.
Blend honey, water and oil; heat slightly.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir until combined evenly.
Heat slowly at 225° to 250° for 2 hours. Turn with spatula every 15 minutes.
Makes 14 (approximately 1/2 cup) servings.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In a large bowl, mix zucchini, all-purpose baking mix, onion, salt, eggs, Cheddar cheese, vegetable oil and garlic. Spread zucchini mixture into the prepared baking dish. Bake
in the preheated oven 25 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned. Cut into bite-sized pieces to serve.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix
Dream
Whip
with powdered Jell-O.
Cut angel food cake in	half
to
make	2
layers and cover it with the Dream Whip/Jell-O mixture like you do frosting.
Decorate the top of cake
with	fruit.	Serve
remaining
fruit
with cake slices. Easy and delicious!

title: stuffed potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool until you can handle them.
Meanwhile, fry bacon and cut cheese.
When potatoes have cooled, peel.
Mash lightly in a large bowl.
Add butter and milk; stir.
Potatoes will still be slightly lumpy.
Stir in bacon and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper. Put mixture in a 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix in an extra large bowl.
Pour ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until bubbly and brown.

title: refrigerator pickles(makes about 8 pints)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and stir to dissolve sugar and salt. Pour over the sliced cucumber and onions.
Keep in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: baked beans casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup mix, water, catsup and vinegar in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in ground beef.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: far east celery casserole *
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Add water chestnuts (drained and sliced), soup and pimiento.
Pour into 1-quart greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, top with melted margarine, bread crumbs and toasted almonds mixed together.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain and add enough concentrated orange juice to make 3 cups. Cook juice with 1 package of tapioca and vanilla pudding mixes. Add fruit and chill.

title: snickers ice cream
directions: Melt and cool Snickers candy bars.
Mix candy bars, Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and regular milk.
Place in a 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze as usual.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In large baking pan, dump two cans of cherry pie filling. Spread out evenly.
On top of cherries, sprinkle cake mix.
Next spread coconut on top of cake mix.
Add nuts.
Melt margarine and spoon on top.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: danish puffs
directions: Measure into bowl 1 cup flour.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water.
Mix with fork.
Round into ball and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 large strips, 3 x 12-inch.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Put in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil the 1 cup water and 1/2 cup butter.
Add the almond extract and remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup flour immediately to keep from lumping.
Beat when smooth and thick.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Divide in half and spread evenly over each piece of pastry.
Bake in a 350° oven until topping is crisp and nicely browned (about 60 minutes).
Frost with confectioners sugar and sprinkle with nuts.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine and serve with salad dressing.

title: corn stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine corn, crumbs, onion and salt; fill pork chops.
Heat slowly; add hot water.
Cover skillet and simmer 40 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Cover; bring to a boil and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Drain.
Saute chopped green onions in butter. Remove from heat.
Add cheese spread, sour cream and milk.
Blend well.
Stir in carrots.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Beat egg, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini, then flour (sifted) with salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° in loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat 1/2 of 1 roll cookie dough in pan and bake as directed on package.
Use 1/2 dough for round pizza pan, all for 18 x 12-inch. Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and coconut. Spread mixture on cooled cookie dough.
Spread strawberry pie filling or glaze on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add any fruit as desired.
Drain fruit if canned.
I use kiwi, apples, pears, pineapple, peaches, strawberries and maraschino cherries.

title: old-time strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift
together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles
coarse
crumbs.
Combine
egg and cream.
Add, stirring just until
dough
follows
the
fork
around bowl.
Roll on lightly floured surface to
1-inch
thickness
(or put in pie tin and bake); cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Bake
on ungreased sheet at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. When done, split.
Spoon berries between layers and on top.
Serve with milk or whipped cream.
This was luscious when served at home!

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, karo and cream of tartar. Bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes. Add soda and stir. It will foam up. Pour over 6 to 8 cups popped corn. Stir until well coated. Bake at 200° for about 1 hour. Stir occasionally.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Drain and cool.
Boil eggs and chop.
Mix all ingredients.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
In large baking pan, shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour; add salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or 9-inch layer pan. Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Spread crushed pineapple over brown sugar mixture.
If using sliced pineapple, arrange over brown sugar mixture and place a half slice of maraschino cherry in center of pineapple slice.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute pineapple juice for water.
Pour batter over pineapple mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool cake 5 minutes before inverting over serving plate.
Let stand 1 minute before removing pan.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti with meatballs
directions: Saute onions and garlic in a
Dutch oven until onions are transparent.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for several hours.

title: crunchy taco mix
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan in oven (3 to 4 minutes). Stir in seasoning mix. Add cereal; stir to coat evenly. Bake, stirring after half the time, for 10 to 12 minutes or until cereal is crisp.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk.
Blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water.
Stir until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring, for five minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Spread small amount of mixture on the bottom of your casserole dish, cover with a layer of vanilla wafers.
Top with layers of bananas.
Cover with custard.
Make 3 layers of each.
End with a layer of custard. Garnish with crumbs of wafers on top.
Let your banana pudding cool for 1/2 hour, and it is ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer vegetables.
Mix dressing and sugar.
Spread over top. Sprinkle bacon over this and then top with cheese.
Chill.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Scrape down sides occasionally. Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with assorted fruits.

title: camp stew(the easy way)
directions: You may add some hot sauce, if desired.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs, milk and salt.
Add remaining ingredients slowly until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with favorite frosting or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Combine ingredients. Use to marinade beef, pork or chicken. Marinate overnight.

title: leta's pulled candy
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until mixture turns brittle when dropped into water.
Add flavoring and soda.
Beat.
Pour on buttered platter.
Turn in edges when cool enough to handle.
Pull until white and brittle.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Boil vinegar and honey.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until thick.

title: chicken and rice a l'orange
directions: In a 9 x 15-inch baking pan (ungreased), put the raw rice. On top of rice, put the chickens, skin side up.
Mix together the mushroom soup and orange juice; pour over chicken and rice. Sprinkle the onion soup mix over top.
Cover with foil; bake for about 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tomato pie
directions: Place the tomato, onion, basil and chives in the bottom of the cooked pie shell.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and 1 cup of the cheese together and spread on top of the tomato/onion layer. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and mix thoroughly. Prepare 1 day in advance.
Store in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch icing
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar slowly.
Add milk and boil for 2 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all together well.
Use a little juice from clams if too stiff.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage and leek soup
directions: Halve leeks lengthwise and chop thin.
Wash in a large bowl of cold water, lift out and drain well in a colander.
Cook carrot and celery in 1/2 stick butter in a 4 or 5 qt. heavy saucepan over moderate heat for about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally until softened.
Add leeks and cook, stirring until softened, about 3 minutes.
Add stock and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for 15 minutes.
While stock simmers, peel potatoes and cut into 1/2 inch cubes.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter in a small heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and cook roux, whisking, 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups simmering stock, whisking vigorously.
Then whisk flour mixture into remaining stock and return to a simmer.
Add potatoes, Kielbasa and marjoram.
Simmer soup, partially covered, until potatoes are tender, 10 - 15 minutes.
Season with salt and white pepper.
Serves 6.
Active time 20 minutes.
Start to finish 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash, then add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil yams 45 to 60 minutes.
Peel and chop to large pieces. Add marshmallows, walnuts and brown sugar.
Stir.
Put in baking dish. Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with juice, beating thoroughly.
Add 1 teaspoon grated orange rind.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream together butter and both sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and oat mixture.
Sift together rest of dry ingredients.
Add to oat mixture; beat 2 minutes.
Put into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine peaches and 1 cup of sugar. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix until all lumps are gone.
Pour over margarine. Spoon fruit on top of batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, milk or whipped cream.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line an 8-inch square baking pan with aluminum foil overlapping at two ends by 1 1/2-inches.
Spray foil with nonstick spray.
Sift together first 4 ingredients onto wax paper.
Combine chocolate and margarine in saucepan over lowest heat, stirring frequently until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup, water and vanilla until well blended.
Beat egg whites into chocolate mixture using a wooden spoon.
Gently stir dry ingredients into chocolate mixture just until well blended and smooth.
Pour batter into pan, spreading evenly to edges.
Bake on middle oven rack for 24 to 28 minutes until center top is almost firm.
Let pan stand on cooking rack for 15 minutes.
Using overhanging foil as handles, lift brownie slab from pan to cooling rack.
Cool completely.
Peel off aluminum foil and cut slab into 12 equal bars.

title: crunchy cucumber sticks
directions: Use fully grown cucumbers too large for pickling.
Peel, cut out seed and cut into sticks or chunks.

title: noodle bake
directions: Boil noodles per package directions.
Drain; add sour cream and cottage cheese.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato puree.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 noodle mixture, chopped green onions, all of meat mixture, 1/2 noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: debbie's german chocolate pie
directions: Heat coconut, pecans, brown sugar and butter, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Spread in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes until bubbly.
Cool.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients except whipped topping.
Cook as directed on the pudding mix for pie.
Cool for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover surface with plastic wrap.
Chill at least 4 hours. To serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: neapolitan pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Beat the cream cheese and eggs until smooth.
Add dry cake mix and milk; beat until well blended.
Divide mix into 3 bowls.
Add dry chocolate mix into one; add dry strawberry mix into second.
Add vanilla to the third.
Pour into pan in layers (do not mix).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Test with toothpick to see if done.
Cool upright in pan for 15 minutes, then remove and cool completely. May be glazed, sprinkled with powdered sugar or eaten plain.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and add remaining ingredients.
After all ingredients are mixed together, drop small amounts (ball-shaped) onto wax paper.
Let top dry, then turn over and let the bottom dry.
Can freeze!

title: oven fried chicken italian style
directions: Rub
all
sides
of chicken generously with mayonnaise. Combine
cheese
and
oregano
and	put in plastic bag.
Shake chicken pieces
one at a time in mix in plastic bag.
Place on broiler rack
in pan 2 inches apart and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: meatballs italiano
directions: In large bowl combine beef, eggs, water, 1/2 cup of bread crumbs, onion, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Measure out 1/4 cup of the mixture, form into a ball.
Roll meatball in remaining bread crumbs to coat.
Repeat with remaining meat mixture and bread crumbs.
Make meatballs, then set aside.
In a large skillet heat oil until hot.
Add meatballs; brown on all sides about 15 minutes.
Drain.
In large saucepan or Dutch oven add spaghetti sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, add the meatballs and simmer covered about 20 minutes.
Stir about every 5 minutes to prevent sticking.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat until creamy.
Add soda dissolved in vinegar.
Add vanilla and then add flour gradually to make a stiff batter that can be rolled very thin.
Cut out and bake in moderate (350°) oven until brown.
They are very crisp and continue to taste fresh after 2 weeks.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine beef, cornflake crumbs, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and minced onion.
Blend well.
Form into small balls the size of walnuts.
Place on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut meat in half crosswise for easier handling.
Mix dry mustard, salt and pepper; pound seasonings into meat.
In heavy 12-inch skillet, quickly brown steak on both sides in hot oil; drain off excess fat.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water, if needed, to equal 1/2 cup.
Add mushroom liquid and Worcestershire sauce to skillet. Cover; simmer until meat is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
During the last few minutes, add mushrooms; heat through.
Skim fat from pan juices before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ashley's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, chips, milk and peanut butter.
Stir with a spoon until well mixed.
Drop spoonfuls on wax paper.
Chill.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: apple custard
directions: Pare, core and quarter Pippins.
Stew among them the yellow peel of a large lemon, grated very fine, and stew them until tender in a very small portion of water.
When done, mash them smooth with the back of a spoon (you must have a pint and a half of the stewed apple); mix sugar with them and set them away until cold.
Beat eggs very light and stir them gradually into milk, alternately with the stewed apples.
Put the mixture into cups, or into a deep dish and bake it about twenty minutes.
Send it to table cold, with nutmeg grated over the top.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Cool.
Toss lightly with next 8 ingredients.
Cover.
Chill.
Garnish with the peanuts. Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, garlic salt and pepper in order given. Pour liquid over vegetables and toss.
Chill for several hours.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup onion.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Mash in beans with liquid.
Heat.
Garnish with remaining chopped onion, cheese and olives.
Serve hot as a spread with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: beans and franks casserole
directions: Drain liquid from the 3 cans of beans and put in large rectangular (glass) baking dish.
To beans, add dry mustard, ketchup, maple syrup (and optional diced green pepper, if desired).
Mix well.
At this point, lay slices of cooked bacon strips on top of beans, if desired.
Line up cocktail franks like little soldiers.

title: "koulourakia" - easter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add oil and beat.
Add eggs all at once and beat again.
Mix baking powder with flour, adding dash or so of nutmeg.
Add cognac to creamed butter mixture, then start adding flour and milk.*
Brush tops of cookies with egg wash and sprinkle them with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or so.

title: chicken casserole(microwave version)
directions: Place soup,
mayonnaise
and
curry powder in a 2 quart casserole and
mix well.
Add frozen vegetables.
Do not cook, just break	apart.	Add
chicken
or turkey.
Spread cheese on top and then cornflakes, margarine and parsley.
Microwave for 35 minutes on	Medium.
(In
regular oven, bake at 375° for 45 minutes.)

title: 5 layer cookies
directions: Mix butter and graham cracker crumbs together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips over graham cracker crust. Spread coconut over chocolate.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top of chips and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tubetti with peas
directions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add the pasta and cook until al dente.
About 4 minutes before pasta is done, add peas.
Drain.

title: corned beef
directions: Place corned beef in pot.
Cut oranges and lemons into thick slices and place around meat.
Pour whole box of pickling spice on top of meat/fruit mixture.
Cover meat with water.
Add black pepper.
Cover tightly; simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat from broth; cool slightly.
Slather with mustard, then pat on brown sugar.
Brown in oven for 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove and cool.
Serves 20 to 25 if sliced thin for sandwiches.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil together sugar, vinegar, celery seed and dill seed.
Pour over kraut and other vegetables while liquid is hot.
Stir well. Refrigerate until cold.

title: fudge hugs
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Stir in flour and milk, nuts and vanilla.
Take about a tablespoon of dough and wrap around hug.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Melt the white chocolate and strip on top of each cookie.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in shallow baking dish.
Scald milk with butter, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle onions and cheese over potatoes; pour on milk and seasonings.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate oatmeal muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar (3 tablespoons), baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
In small bowl, combine eggs, oil, applesauce and vanilla and mix remaining sugar until well blended.
Add to flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Spoon into paper lined microwave-safe pans, filling each about 2/3 full. Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: fried yellow squash
directions: Wash and slice the squash. Put corn meal into Ziploc bag. Dip the squash into combined egg and milk mixture and fry them slowly in grease. You don't want the grease too deep, just enough to cook the squash on both sides; repeat each thing over, adding grease before each frying.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients, stirring well.
Add milk.
Fold in bananas, nuts and vanilla. Bake in 9 x 13-inch or 3 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured. Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add to tomato sauce and Ragu meat sauce in saucepan.
Add garlic salt and salt and pepper, then add 8 ounce can of water.
Cook 1 1/2 hours until it is cooked down.
Serve with long spaghetti.

title: chicken-shrimp casserole
directions: Boil, bone and halve chicken breasts.
Place on bottom of greased, large glass baking dish.
Top with shrimp and artichokes. Saute onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Melt remaining 5 tablespoons of butter and add flour.
Whisk and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Slowly add warmed milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Stir in tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Pour over chicken mixture and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pizzelles
directions: Melt butter; cool.
Beat eggs, extracts, sugar and cooled butter together.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth; batter will be very soft.
Spoon 1 teaspoon batter to the iron at a time.
Makes about 8 to 10 dozen pizzelles.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Just stir until ingredients are mixed.
Bake at 375° for 23 minutes in a 2-quart greased baking dish (metal pan may vary). Ice while hot with white Butter Icing.

title: california rolls(yield 3 dozen)
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water in a large bowl.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add beaten eggs, salt, flour and butter.
Mix well. Let stand over night.
(DO NOT REFRIGERATE.)

title: beefy biscuit cups
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce. Cook over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through. Press biscuits onto the bottom and up the sides of greased muffin cups. Spoon 2 tablespoons meat mixture into the center of each cup. Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 3 minutes longer.

title: blueberry chicken or pork chops
directions: Cut chicken into chicken fingers.
Brown in oil.
Add vinegar and broth, cook 15 to 20 minutes, until done, uncovered.
Make sauce with cream and flour.
Add to chicken; cook until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
May garnish with berries.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix onion, pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce together in small bowl.
Pour hot vegetable oil over this and then add to other ingredients.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top of casserole.
Bake at 300° approximately 30 minutes.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, lemon rind and cornstarch.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add to boiling water.
Bring to boil; boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell and top with beaten egg whites.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Put in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over apples.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cut butter into dry ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add buttermilk and mix well.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Shape into 1 round of 7-inches.
Place on lightly oiled baking sheet. Mark top with a cross.
Bake in top 1/3 of the oven at 400° for 45 minutes or until bottom sounds hollow.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well and fry like pancakes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl, flour, sugar and salt.
Mix in saucepan, margarine or butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add to mixture in bowl and beat well.
Add sour cream, eggs and baking soda.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in an 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan (shallow).

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook and cut up chicken in fairly large pieces. Cut up cheese. Cook broccoli according to directions.

title: strawberry slide
directions: 1st Layer: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 13 x 9 pan. Chill. Save a few crumbs for topping.

title: buttermilk refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
Melt shortening in microwave and mix with buttermilk. Add to yeast mixture.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart dish with Pam.
In a large bowl, combine soup, broth, onion, celery and chestnuts.
Stir to blend.
Add chicken, noodles and nuts.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with Durkee French fried onion rings and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: brunswick stew 2
directions: Mix everything together in a big pot.
Cook over medium heat. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli on High for 5 minutes.
In baking dish, add rice, onion, milk, soup, chicken and half of the cheese to broccoli.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand in refrigerator.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and saute.
Brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 45 minutes over low heat covered.
Serve in deep bowls topped with toasted French bread.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together in pan.
Add vanilla, butter and 1/4 cup milk and boil 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Beat pudding and 3 cups milk until pudding begins to thicken.
Add Cool Whip. In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers, pudding mixture, crackers, pudding mixture and crackers.
Pour icing over top. Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: egg-sausage brunch
directions: Put slices of bread in greased casserole.
Pour eggs, milk, pepper and mustard over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Saute sausage, onion and mushrooms.
Bake eggs and bread at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add sausage.
Layer cheeses and chips.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Pass the picante.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery until well cooked.
Simmer first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Blend well in blender.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste and reheat for about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: the best scratch pancakes
directions: Place all in bowl; stir.
Use the milk to make a batter thin enough to pour.
Heat skillet to 350° (electric skillet best). Melt 1/4 slice margarine in hot skillet, then pour in 1/2 cup batter to make large pancake.
(Big spoon size nice about 4 to regular skillet.)
Watch as bubbles form, then turn.
Brown well on both sides.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cook frozen vegetables.
Place artichoke hearts in bottom of a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cream cheese, butter and lemon juice.
Add spinach to cheese mixture and put in casserole. Put croutons on top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mild salsa
directions: Grind everything and mix.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick.
Pack in hot canning jars.
Put on hot lids and rings; hot water bath for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine Crisco, butter and water; bring to a rolling boil. Add flour, all at once, stirring until mixture leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball; cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.

title: texas pan handle cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, bell pepper - set aside.

title: shrimp jello salad
directions: In blender, set on stir, dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water, tomato soup, vinegar and chili sauce; blend.
Add cream cheese, one cube at a time, while blending.

title: bread and butter cucumber pickles
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, over high heat, heat sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery and mustard seed to boiling, stirring often.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Store in covered glass container in refrigerator and use within one month. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl layer the following ingredients:

head of lettuce (broken into bite-size pieces), head of broccoli (cut into bite size florets), onion (sliced into small pieces), spread mayonnaise over top of onion, sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise, shake Parmesan cheese over top of sugar, crumble bacon on top. Refrigerate in layers overnight.
Mix ingredients together right before serving.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add enough water for brown gravy.
Cook for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This serves 3,800 people.
If more are expected add the 2 rabbits, but only if necessary, because most people don't like hares in their stew.

title: one step chocolate cake roll(club member: terah)
directions: Line 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil. Grease foil.
In medium bowl, combine condensed milk, 2 egg yolks, coconut, nuts, margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix well.
Spread in pan. In large bowl, beat 3 eggs at high speed until fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar, then beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except confectioners sugar. Beat 1 minute. Pour evenly over coconut mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with confectioner sugar.

Immediately turn onto towel. Peel off foil, begin at narrow end and roll up cake, jelly roll fashion. Place on serving plate, seam side down; cool. Sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar and drizzle with chocolate glaze.

title: pecan pie
directions: Have butter very soft.
Beat eggs lightly without separating and add sugar, Karo, butter and vanilla.
Mix well; stir in pecans.
Spread in pie crust.
Bake for one hour in a 325° oven.

title: grandma's chocolate fudge
directions: Cook over slow heat the sugar, cocoa, flour, syrup and milk until it forms a soft ball when tried in cold water.
Stir only until sugar is melted.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Let stand a few minutes.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into pieces while still warm and soft.

title: our favorite french casserole
directions: *You may use canned tomatoes.

title: easy chicken supper
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place bread crumbs on sheet of wax paper.
In shallow bowl or pie plate, beat mayonnaise and milk until smooth.
Dip chicken breasts into mayonnaise mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place chicken in pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over; bake for 20 minutes, until juices run clear.
(Cooking time will vary, depending on size and thickness of chicken.)

title: oatmeal cake with broiled frosting
directions: Pour water over oats; let stand 20 minutes. Cream sugars and butter; add to oatmeal mixture. Beat eggs and add. Sift all dry ingredients. Add to oatmeal mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla. Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Drop 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 envelope Lipton onion soup.
Add chicken pieces.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with two cans of water.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt and mix together chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Keep warm.
In another pan bring to a slow boil the butter, evaporated milk and vanilla pudding.
Add the powdered sugar.
Pour 1/2 the chips mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Let cool.
Pat the creamed mixture on top.
Add the Spanish peanuts to the other half of chips mixture and pour on top. Refrigerate.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Cook onion in water until tender, about 5 minutes; drain.
In a bowl combine eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper, oregano and hot sauce.
Stir in onion, cheese and artichokes.
Spread in well-greased baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven for 17 to 18 minutes. (Test at this time, it may need longer.)
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Garnish with pimento strips, if desired.
Good hot or cold.
Makes about 60 small squares.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg at low speed until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cotton pickin' good cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil together and pour into greased pan(s). Best as a 2 layer cake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, crumbling as you brown; drain.
Mix together sausage, consomme, French onion soup and raw rice.
Place in casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups water with spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown meat;
drain fat.
Add
the
rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Spread on rye rounds and warm in oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together in large bowl the sugar, oil, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla, pumpkin, baking soda, salt and eggs.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 5 mini pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate-caramel tortillas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly coat cookie sheet(s) with nonstick cooking spray.
Stack tortillas and cut in 8 wedges (you'll have 48).
Arrange wedges in a single layer on prepared cookie sheet(s).
Lightly spray tops with cooking spray.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes, until golden and crisp. Slide onto oven rack to cool.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Mix broken crackers and milk in mixing bowl.
Allow crackers to take up milk.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into desired size loaf.
Bake on broiler rack lined with foil. Pierce foil for fat to drop into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chunky chicken-potato soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Place half of potato mixture in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Top with cover and process until smooth.
Add pureed mixture, chicken and milk to Dutch oven; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in pimento. Ladle soup into serving bowls.
Top each serving with 2 teaspoons of sour cream, 2 teaspoons cheese and 1 teaspoon chives.
Yields 8 cups.

title: zesty baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: twix bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Punch holes in hot cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over cake. Let cool completely.
Spread caramel topping over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over topping.
Sprinkle crushed Twix bars over Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: onion soup or seasoning mix
directions: Store in foil packet in cool, dry place.
Makes 1 envelope.

title: lasagne(microwave)
directions: Cook hamburger or ground turkey.
Add spaghetti sauce, garlic and basil.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Stir and cook on Full power 7 to 8 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Stir well; roll out on breadboard.
Heat vegetable oil to 380°; drop rolled and thin cut triangles into oil.
Deep fry for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Unwrap caramels and place in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes, stir well and add milk to caramels. Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered wax paper.
Cool, cover and chill.
Combine chocolate morsels and Crisco in 4-cup glass measure.
Microwave at Medium 3 to 4 minutes or until morsels are softened; stir well.
Dip caramel centers into chocolate; return to wax paper.
Chill. Store candy in refrigerator.
Yield: about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook onions and ground beef until soft and browned.
Crumble with a fork and stir in ketchup, mustard and soup.
Heat until it bubbles and serve on buns.

title: raw veggie dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well, then fold in sour cream.
Chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese and mix well.
In a flat casserole dish, layer corn mixture and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften and place in middle of dish (or serving tray).
Sprinkle drained crab meat over the cream cheese. Pour cocktail sauce evenly over crab meat and cream cheese.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: crawfish and corn soup
directions: Mix Butter Buds in water and heat over low heat.
Add chicken bouillon.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Blend cornstarch with skim milk.
Add evaporated milk and stir until well blended and slightly thickened.
Add corn, crawfish, Worcestershire, Tabasco and salt.
Cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: First layer:
Crush wafers; mix with 1 stick of melted margarine and line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chow chow
directions: Press out the juice in tomatoes. Cook 30 minutes and put in jars.

title: cherry oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, nuts, oats, margarine and flour until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remainder into bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Stir cinnamon into cherry filling.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top, pressing lightly.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: mushroom turnovers
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter thoroughly.
Add flour and work until smooth.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Fill with 1 teaspoon filling.
Press edges together with fork and prick top to release steam.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Pull chicken from bone and chop finely.
Mix chicken, eggs, celery, onion and pimentos into large mixing bowl.
Add seasoned salt, garlic and approximately 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.

title: no-fat chicken salad oriental
directions: In mixing bowl, combine chicken, 1/2 cup orange segments, water chestnuts, 2 tablespoons green onion and red pepper.
Next, combine yogurt, banana, honey, lemon juice, vinegar, ginger and white pepper in blender.
Puree until smooth.
Pour over chicken; mix well and chill.

title: oriental stir-fried hamburger and mushrooms
directions: Spray a large nonstick skillet or electric frypan with cooking spray for no-fat frying.
Spread meat in skillet; cook over medium heat until underside is brown.
Break into chunks and drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Uncover and continue to cook, stirring frequently until nearly all liquid evaporates.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frosted caramel nut braid
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add milk, eggs, sugar, butter, salt and 2 cups flour; beat on medium speed for 3 minutes. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft but sticky dough. DO NOT KNEAD. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Beat 25 strokes with a heavy spoon, turn onto a well-floured surface. Roll into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle. Combine pecans, butter, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons of flour with a fork; spread evenly over the entire surface of dough. Cut dough lengthwise into three strips. Roll up each strip jellyroll style, beginning at long end. Pinch edges and ends to seal. Place three rolls, lengthwise, diagonally, seam-side down, on a foil-lined baking pan. Braid ropes together gently (do not stretch); seal ends. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly on a wire rack.

title: tuna fish ball spread
directions: Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Form into ball. Roll in chopped parsley or chopped nuts.
Spread on crackers.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add vegetable oil, water, yogurt, egg substitute and lemon juice. Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.

Pour batter into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Drizzle with Lemon Glaze.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and let set until dissolved. Add 3 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Knead until smooth.
Put in lrg. greased bowl.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and divide into 2 equal parts.
Spread out on greased pizza pans or cookie sheets.
Makes 2 pizzas or cut into pizza sticks. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes after putting toppings on, cheese last.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Freeze.
Add 2 liters chilled 7-Up or ginger ale when ready to serve.
Remove banana mixture from freezer 3 hours before serving.
Serves 30.

title: best ever sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes, quarter and cover or put enough water in them to cook until tender.
Remove from heat and if there is any water left, drain it off.
Mash and sweeten to taste.
Crush enough corn flakes and add to potatoes to make them firm enough to handle. Form balls and put 1/2 of a marshmallow in center and cover completely.
Roll in crushed corn flakes and brown in hot oil.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears through coarse food chopper; let drip until excess juice is removed.
Grind peppers and onions; combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil; cook 20 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cream 3 oz cream cheese with 3 tbsp milk until smooth.
Spread in bottom of baked 8-inch pie shell.
Press quart strawberries into cream cheese.
Crush remaining half of berries with 1 cup sugar and 3 tbsp cornstarch.
Cook until thick; add 2 tbsp butter.
Cool; then spread over berries in w/and the cream cheese.
Chill several hours.

title: cherry kuchen
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour to mixture.
Spread 3/4 of the batter on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon on pie filling.
Drop remaining fourth of batter on top.
(It spreads as it bakes.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, tartar and salt; cut in shortening. Add milk.
Mix until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on floured surface, knead gently and roll out.
Cut and bake on ungreased sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: barbecue bean bake
directions: Saute bacon, hamburg and onions.
In a large container combine all beans.
Add mustard, ketchup, chili sauce, chili powder and molasses.
Mix together with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves an army.

title: breakfast
directions: Cut up the potatoes and brown in a little oil.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute the onion and green pepper.
Place on top of the potatoes.
Cut up the ham.
Place on top of previous layers. Scramble the eggs, softly; don't cook dry, leave moist.
Place on top of ham.
Sprinkle the cheese on top. Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon and basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine oil and next seven ingredients in shallow baking dish. Add chicken making sure to coat both sides.
Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.
Prepare charcoal for grilling or heat broiler.
Grill or broil chicken 4 inches from heat, turning once, 3 to 5 minutes per side or until completely cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coke salad
directions: Place cherries, water and cola in pan and boil for a few minutes.
Pour over jello and when cool, add pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate to set.

title: chunk pickles
directions: Use cucumbers that are beginning to turn yellow.
Do not peel them. Cut out seeds and pulp.
Cut into 4-inch cubes.

title: shrimp and oyster gumbo
directions: If using fresh shrimps, peel them and season GENEROUSLY with salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Set aside till ready to use.

title: miss ruthie's chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Boil egg noodles in chicken broth. Melt together all other ingredients.
Add noodles, 1 cup broth and deboned chicken.

title: banana yogurt shake
directions: In a blender, combine ingredients; blend until smooth.
Serve.

title: inexpensive sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs till lemon in color.
Add sugar, vanilla, and salt. With mixer running add 1 cup BOILING milk with butter.
Sift in 2 cups flour and mix well.
Pour into cake pan and bake for 35 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: hummus from dried chickpeas *
directions: Soak chickpeas in water to cover and baking soda overnight. Add water to cover by several inches to chickpeas and simmer one hour.
Drain, saving about one cup water.
Puree all ingredients except paprika in food processor, adding 1/4 cup reserved water. Place in serving bowl and sprinkle with paprika.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, salt and cream of tartar.
Cover and let boil 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Boil without stirring to firm ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Pour slowly, beating constantly, over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture holds it shape when dropped from spoon.
Add flavoring and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need a punch bowl.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, save drippings, drain on paper towels and crumble.
Cook onions in drippings over medium heat until translucent.
Stir in flour, cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring, until mixture is golden.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly with a whisk.
When mixture is thickened reduce heat to a simmer.
Add bacon, potatoes, cream, spices, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, Do not boil.
Add cheese and onion. Stir until cheese is melted into soup.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Using a mixing bowl, beat the egg yolks and add milk.
Sift sugar, flour, cocoa and salt and place in top of double boiler. Stir 1/3 cup of milk and egg mixture into dry ingredients to form smooth paste, then stir in remaining liquid.
Cook until mixture thickens, then add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown lightly in moderate oven at 325°.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add eggs, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Add meat.
Mix well again.
Form into loaf and place in greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Cover meat loaf with Piquant Sauce and bake for 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together peanut butter, brown sugar and confectioners sugar.
Roll into small balls; flatten.
Melt chips and shortening together in microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Put in flattened balls; add more chocolate mixture on top.
Put in fridge.

title: chicken tortilla pie
directions: Slice tortillas into 1/2-inch strips, set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl.
Next make layers of strips, then your mixture, etc., until all ingredients are used in a baking pan or dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces; cook well.
Combine cooked chicken, cream soup, 1/2 can milk and cut vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place biscuits on top of mixture, bake for 20 more minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir with spoon until thoroughly moistened.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten to 1/4 inch thickness using glass -- the bottom dipped in flour.
Bake for 6-8 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Frost when cool and sprinkle with candy bits.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken; dice.
Save 2 cups chicken broth, then add the Ro-Tel tomatoes and mushroom soup.
Mix bell peppers and onions together in a bowl.
Take a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Add Fritos; sprinkle bell peppers and onions, then add cream of mushroom mixture.
Alternate layers until dish is full.
Bake for about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°, then add cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: frozen banana cream salad
directions: Soften cheese; add mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Beat until creamy.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into individual molds and freeze.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind all together.
Add salt, brown sugar and vinegar to taste.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes after it comes to a boil.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: *Ro-Tel is tomatoes with green chilies.

title: raspberry cheese appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients together. Press into container. Cover. Refrigerate 2 hours +.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in baking dish.
Pour celery soup over broccoli. Sprinkle salt over this.
Add a pat of butter.
Cover with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dinner
directions: For chili meat:
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato juice, chili mix and garlic salt to taste.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in water and add to 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add half of the flour and half the buttermilk.
Blend well.
Add the remaining flour and milk; mix.
Blend in flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: peg's chicken in a bundle
directions: Great on grill or in oven!
Easy!

title: waldensian salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and chip of garlic.
Chill overnight.
Break lettuce.
Add 1/2 jar parsley.
Pour vinegar mixture over lettuce and mix well.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs with a fork first.
Add sugar and then oil.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Put batter into muffin papers and fill with batter.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: prisnic
directions: Cook California Blend.
Beat the eggs.
Add the flour.
Add cottage cheese, butter and Velveeta.
Fold into vegetables.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Toast pecans for 30 minutes at 250°. Slice butter over top of pecans. Stir until coated. Sprinkle with salt and toast for 1 hour.

title: no cook noodles lasagna
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion in skillet; add spaghetti sauce. In separate bowl, mix cheese and eggs.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

Layer noodles, meat and cheese in dish. Start with uncooked noodles, then meat, next cheeses, then noodles and top with meat mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Double wrap dish with heavy microwavable plastic wrap.
Bake in microwave 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus
directions: With top of chafing dish set in water pan, heat cream.
Blend flour and butter and stir into hot cream.
Add seasonings, chicken and asparagus.
When very hot, serve on split buttered biscuits. Serves 4.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Soften margarine; add cheese and mix.
Add flour and other ingredients slowly.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll in balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown. Remove from a cookie sheet and place on paper towels to cool.

title: summer pasta
directions: Saut carrots, onions, parsley, basil and garlic for 15 minutes; cover and simmer for 15 more minutes.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, bell pepper, wine, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 45 minutes.
In separate pan, melt butter; add flour.
Cook roux over very low heat; whisk in heated cream.
Add tomato paste and whisk until mixture is very smooth.
Stir into veggies along with Parmesan cheese.
Toss mixture with cooked pasta.

title: lera's punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour over sherbet.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all vegetables and add to cooked spaghetti.
Add 1 bottle of Italian dressing and 1 jar salad topping.
Mix well. Keeps for several days in refrigerator.
Better if made 2 or 3 days before using.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325°.
When cool, ice with:

title: chewy scotch squares(cookies)
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Melt butter or margarine. Add brown sugar; stir until dissolved.
Stir in preserves.
Add oats and the dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cover baking sheet with foil, turn up edges 1/2-inch.
Spread dough in center to 6-inch square.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Dough will spread during baking.
Cool 15 minutes, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: french apple bread pudding
directions: Mix together and let set until bread absorbs the liquid.
Bake 1 hour in 9-inch square pan at 350°.

title: basic red beans(crock-pot)
directions: The night before beans are to be used, wash and sort dried beans.
Wash 2 to 3 times, alternating between crock-pot and colander.
When water runs clear, cover beans in crock-pot with about 2-inches of cold water. Add whole peeled onion.
Turn crock-pot to low and allow to cook overnight.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, oranges, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until well done.
Cool. Combine butternut flavoring, pineapple and pudding mix.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cake. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or overnite. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: pork tenderloins with dilled mushroom sauce
directions: Cut each tenderloin crosswise in 4 pieces.
Place each piece, cut side down, on a flat surface and flatten with mallet or cleaver to 1/2-inch thick.
In large skillet, cook mushrooms in butter over medium-high heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon to small bowl; cover and reserve.
Brown tenderloin patties in oil in same frying pan, 4 at a time, over medium-high heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Place all browned patties in pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add wine; cover tightly and cook slowly 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove patties to serving platter and keep warm.
Whisk sour cream and dill weed into wine in pan. Add mushrooms and cook slowly until heated through.
Do not boil. Serve sauce with pork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add egg and sugar; mix.
Add chocolate chips; stir and set aside.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in oil, add water and bouillon cubes and heat to boiling.
Add noodles and salt, cook three minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic powder and cook an additional 4 minutes.
Add milk and cheese, stir until smooth.
Serves 6.

title: easy-special-muffins(makes 12 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry
ingredients: pancake mix, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon. Add and mix oil.
Then add chopped apples and raisins. Mix completely.
Fill paper muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: onion smothered steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into meat.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown meat in hot oil in a deep pan to avoid splatter.
Top with onion slices.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf and serve.
Serves 6.

title: munker
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk, then flour with baking powder and almond extract.
Bake in munke iron in butter, turning when half done.
Delicious!

title: emerald cantaloupe
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions, using 1/4 cup less water than indicated.
Chill until partially set; fold in drained pineapple.
Arrange cantaloupe halves on a shallow tray; fill cavities with gelatin mixture and chill until set.
Roll rye crisp with a rolling pin to make fine crumbs and add sugar substitutes and cinnamon.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Using a large bowl, add egg, water, soup, bread crumbs or croutons, ketchup and mustard.
Stir together, then add ground beef and mix well.
Form into loaf.
Bake in shallow pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Mix together sugar, water and Karo. Cook for 3 minutes on FULL power. Add peanuts and cook 10 to 11 minutes on FULL power (soft-ball stage). Add remaining ingredients. Stir until mixture begins to thicken and turns creamy looking. Place on greased cookie sheet or waxed paper until cool.

title: homestead goulash
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, onion, green pepper, celery, seasoning salt, garlic power, Accent and black pepper. Brown mixture in skillet and drain off fat.
Layer mixture in baking pan and top with shredded cheese. Top the cheese with a layer of crushed red pepper and layer that with the mixed vegetables and corn. Smooth on mashed potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: oklahoma dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add cheese until melted. Add other ingredients; mix well.
Serve warm on tortilla chips.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix all ingredients until dry and crumbly with spoon and hands.
Firmly pat into well greased 9 x 9-inch pan half the mixture.
Spread on layer, apricot jam.
Press over this the rest of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick sherbet
directions: Freeze can until solid.
Place under hot water for 1 minute. Open can, put fruit in a blender, and process until it is the consistency of sherbet.
If necessary, return to freezer until serving time.
Serve plain or over melon slices.

title: punch
directions: Pour Kool-Aid into an empty 2 liter bottle.
Pour sugar into bottle with the Kool-Aid.
Fill the bottle of Kool-Aid and sugar with warm water to the top.
Cap bottle and shake really well and freeze overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out all water.
Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with Fritos.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Simmer and serve hot.

title: betty's frosted brownies
directions: Place flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Melt margarine, cocoa and water over medium heat until it bubbles or boils just a little.
Mix together the skim milk, lemon juice, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix flour mixture and margarine-cocoa mixture. Add other mixture to chocolate mixture (will be thin).
Spray a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with Pam.
Pour in brownies; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peppered steak
directions: Brown steak in salad oil.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, add green peppers.

title: wake-up special
directions: Place butter in 2-quart casserole with green peppers.
Saute in Radarange oven 30 seconds.
Stir eggs and soup together.
Blend into sauteed mixture.
Cook in Radarange oven 4 1/2 to 5 minutes. Stir every 2 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix the sugar and Crisco together until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix in flour and liquids alternately, ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 4 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour juice from can of pineapple (used in icing) over layers.
Ice with Pineapple Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat well together.
Add enough homogenized milk to almost fill canister to freezer.
Recipe for a 4-quart freezer.

title: salmon sandwiches
directions: Mix salmon, green pepper, peanuts, onions, 1/3 cup chili sauce, mustard and pepper sauce.
Cut or tear breads crosswise into halves.
Fill each half with about 1/4 cup lettuce and 1/4 cup salmon mixture.
Top with alfalfa sprouts.
Serve with chili sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Peel zucchini; grate.
Mix everything together real well. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Put zucchini mixture in jars. Cold pack 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: wild rice with carrots and onions
directions: In small saucepan combine rice with salt and 1 cup cold water, bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, 40 to 50 minutes or until tender. Drain if necessary.
While rice is cooking, in a skillet cook carrots in butter over moderate low heat, stirring for 5 minutes. Add onion; cook, stirring for 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in rice, juice and parsley.
Can make 1 day in advance, kept covered and chilled.
In saucepan, reheat with 1 tablespoon water over moderate low heat, stirring until heated.

title: fried rice
directions: In an electric skillet, cook vegetables in margarine until crisp.
Add rice, ham and scrambled eggs.
Stir until heated. Season with salt, pepper and Accent.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place the marmalade, sugar, cranberry juice, water, cinnamon, mustard seed and cloves in a 6-quart nonreactive casserole.
Cover and cook over low heat until every last granule of sugar is dissolved.
Uncover; bring to a boil and boil 1 minute; add the cranberries and cook until they pop.
Cool completely.

title: 3 layer strawberry salad
directions: First layer- Mix together pretzels, margarine and 1/4 c. sugar.
Press into a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: leroy's chocolate bourbon pie
directions: Beat eggs well, gradually adding sugar; add butter and bourbon and blend in cornstarch.
Put bits and nuts into pie shell and pour mix over.
Put into oven at 350°.
This should be a preheated oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: vegan chicken salad
directions: Whiz first 6 items in blender until smooth.
Pour into bowl. Add Vital gluten and mix well.
Will be very thick.
Press into well-oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Tear apart.
Add approximately 8 ounces Vegan chicken to the last 4 items to make a salad.
You may freeze the rest for future use.
If you need a larger amount of salad, just add more of the last 4 ingredients.

title: heavenly, heavenly salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate three hours before serving.

title: lime pear delight
directions: Dissolve lime jello in hot pear juice.
Add sieved pears (put through a sieve) to the softened cream cheese; blend until smooth.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: ground beef and tater casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet (salt and pepper to taste).
Drain.
Mix beef, beans, soup and water.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Mix potatoes and 1/2 can of onions; spoon in a mounded ring around outside edge of casserole.

title: polish cabbage roll
directions: Boil cabbage till outside is tender.
Cook rice and brown ground beef.
Mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: tropical stuffed young turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove giblets and neck from Young turkey; set aside for another use.
Remove and discard excess fat. Wash turkey; dry with paper towels.
Drain pineapple, pouring juices into small saucepan.
Add jelly to juice; set aside. Reserve pineapple.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter.
Add onion and Macadamia nuts; saute until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Add pineapple, rice, currants, ginger and broth; heat through.
Spoon mixture into neck cavity of turkey.
Bring neck skin over stuffing into body cavity; do not pack.
(Place extra stuffing in greased baking dish; cover and bake last 30 minutes turkey bakes.)
Close body cavity with poultry pins.
Lace with string.
Tie legs together.
Pin wings to breast.
Grease rack in roasting pan with cooking spray.
Place turkey, breast side up, on rack.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest portion of thigh away from the bone.
Heat jelly mixture until jelly melts, stirring until blended.
Brush some mixture over turkey.
Roast, uncovered, basting every 30 minutes with jelly mixture, until thermometer registers 170°.
Place turkey on warm serving platter.
Remove pins and string.
Let stand 15 minutes for easier carving.
If desired, garnish with pineapple and papaya slices, lime twists and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gloria's shrimp appetizers
directions: Boil shrimp with dill, lemon, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Soak the mushrooms for 30 minutes; cut off stems and put in blender with tomatoes, scallions, parsley, garlic and ginger.
Put mixture into a bowl with the vinegar, sesame oil and safflower oil.
Add the chili sauce.
Taste.
You may want to add a little more ginger or sesame oil.
(It looks like a coarse chop.)
Peel and devein shrimp and toss with vegetable mixture.
Or use mixture on grilled fish, swordfish particularly, at room temperature.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well. Spoon into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Separate biscuits; place on top of pie. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, covering loosely with foil after 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's punch
directions: Dilute frozen juices per directions.
Add pineapple juice. Pour into punch bowl.
Add ice and ginger ale or soda (2 to 3 bottles per recipe).
