title: pesto-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain; toss with oil.
Mix Pesto, olives, vinegar and tomatoes in large bowl.
Arrange 2 cups macaroni and 2 cups spinach on olive mixture; repeat with remaining macaroni and spinach.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Toss and sprinkle with cheese. Serves 6.

title: fishy mac casserole
directions: Pre-heat oven to 375°.
Make macaroni and cheese per package directions; add tuna and peas and stir well.
Spread mixture into a baking dish.
Lay cheese slices across the top of mixture. Sprinkle corn chips on top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Spread lettuce on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Cut cauliflower into pieces and place on top of lettuce.
Crumble bacon and place on top of cauliflower.
Place sliced onion on top of bacon.
Mix honey and Miracle Whip, blending well.
Pour over the top of the other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let chill for 1 hour.
Form ball and roll in remaining cup of nuts.
Make 2 to 3 days ahead of serving and keep in refrigerator.

title: simply pasta(makes 4 to 8 servings)
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in heavy large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes, dried basil, bouillon cubes and crushed red pepper.
Bring to boil, breaking up tomatoes with back of spoon.
Reduce heat to medium; simmer until mixture thickens to chunky sauce and is reduced to 6 cups, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper. Can be made 2 days ahead.
Cover and chill.
Rewarm over low heat before continuing.

title: wite beans and rice
directions: first put the water in the pot and ster it up.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Keeps a long time.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: tuna baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in halves lengthwise.
Scoop out centers.
Mash potatoes with butter or margarine and enough milk to make potatoes fluffy.
Season with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Blend tuna with potato mixture, fill shells and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper in round slices and mix with cooled carrots.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or more.
Drain to serve.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together then add brown sugar and oil.
Mix all and remove 3/4 cup for topping.
To this 3/4 cup, add cinnamon and chopped nuts; set aside.
To buttermilk, add soda; stir well, then add egg.
Stir well and add to flour mixture. Pour into 1 9 x 13-inch foil-lined pan.
Sprinkle topping on top of coffee cake and press down a bit.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ship wrecked
directions: Place hamburger in baking dish.
Cook in oven at 300° until brown.
Add sliced potatoes, onion, pork and beans, peas, celery, soup and tomato soup. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian delight pie
directions: Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Let sit in refrigerator about 30 minutes.

title: suzanne's fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine eggs, oil, cinnamon, sugar and vanilla and mix thoroughly; mixture will be very thick.
Place in ungreased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
No icing needed; it makes its own crunchy top.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan over medium-low heat until crisp. Drain on absorbent paper. Saute celery in bacon fat 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add flour. Stir until well blended.
Gradually stir in milk. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute longer. Serve topped with crumbled bacon.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sour cream, taco sauce and taco seasoning.
Spread creamed mixture onto a platter.
Dice lettuce.
Spread on top of creamed mixture.
Dice tomatoes. Spread over lettuce.
Shred cheese.
Sprinkle over tomatoes. Serve with taco chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, mayonnaise and pecans.
Place in greased pan.
Mix cheese and chips; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chow-chow
directions: For sweet Chow-Chow, use 3 to 4 red peppers without seeds instead of hot peppers.

title: orange and lemon salad
directions: Quarter unpeeled fruit or cut in small sections as preferred. Place in salad bowl.
Sprinkle lightly with mint, salt and pepper and olive oil.
Place on lettuce leaves and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy apple oatmeal
directions: Place all in a crock-pot and cook overnight, or cook on stovetop according to directions for the kind of oatmeal used. Yields 6 servings.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until blended.
Add Cool Whip, mix well.
Drain cherries and cut in half.
Mix cherries and pineapple with out ingredients.
May use nuts on top.

title: venison roast
directions: Grease small roaster.
Put in vegetables and 1/2 of each kind of soup.
Add 1 cup water and mix together.
Make well in center and push meat down into it.
Top meat with remaining mushroom soup; sprinkle with rest of onion soup.
Cover pan tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles about 9 minutes; drain.
Make white sauce and add 1 cup of grated cheese.
Using a small deep greased casserole, layer noodles, tuna, mushrooms, olives, eggs and white sauce in that order.
Then add another layer of each and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This can also be made ahead of time and put in the refrigerator.
Take out several hours before baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: linguine salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss periodically so it will marinate evenly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: autumn pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Blend flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add eggs, zucchini and onion.
Heat pancake griddle with a little oil.
Drop mixture by large tablespoonfuls onto griddle and spread out like pancakes. Cook until golden on both sides.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Stir together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and melt a stick of margarine and pour over crumbs. Press dampened crumbs over top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda. Cut in margarine; add yeast and buttermilk. Stir to blend. Refrigerate overnight. Knead on floured board. Roll out thickness desired. Cut into biscuits and put in greased pan. Brush tops with melted butter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "believe it" pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered pan.
Pour in hot fruit, seasoned to your taste with sugar and butter.
Bake in hot oven.
Crust comes to top and browns.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave as per package directions. Remove; mix in soup, egg, horseradish, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.	Microwave on High 10 minutes.
Remove; add cheese. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Remove; sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Pour butter over and broil until crumbs are browned.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Press coconut and pecans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cake as directed.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Melt margarine and mix with powdered sugar and softened cream cheese. Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Then add tomato mixture.
Pour in desired container and chill. A mold is nice.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet (drain).
Add other ingredients, except cheese and Doritos.
Bring to boil.
Pour into casserole dish in layers.
Put 1/2 crushed Doritos, cheese and 1/2 meat, then the other 1/2.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Can be frozen.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Beat shortening and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add salt, eggs, bananas, sour cream and baking soda.
Stir in flour.
Pour into pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: *The amount should cover most of the rice, depends on whether you use breasts, or just legs and thighs.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and fold into sour cream.
Chill approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Heat juice from pineapple with sugar.
Cool.
Beat eggs, cream and flour.
Mix this with juice and sugar mixture.
Cook on low heat until thick.
(Cool in refrigerator before mixing with fruit.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add milk and powdered sugar; mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.
Can be eaten immediately.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Saute pecans in margarine; drain on paper towels.
Beat cream cheese at high speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; turn oven off and partially open oven door.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool on a wire rack in a draft-free area.
Cover cheesecake and chill at least 8 hours. Garnish with toasted pecan halves, if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour. Cream the cooking oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas; blend well. Add buttermilk and flour alternately. Blend well.
Add nuts and pour into medium loaf pan (oiled). Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar and yeast.
In second bowl, beat egg, oil and warm water.
Add to flour mixture and stir. Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Make as many rolls as you need. Put remainder of batter in refrigerator.
It will keep about 1 week.
Makes 24 rolls.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix and cook on greased cookie sheet.

title: sauteed rice
directions: Saute rice in butter.
Add other ingredients; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Delicious and easy.

title: chocolate chip cookies(stay soft)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour and chips.
Stir flour in last and follow with chips.
Roll in balls and bake until done at 325°.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with all but 1/4 wafer crumbs.
Cream butter and sugar together; add beaten egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Add strawberry juice; cook to custard stage.
Pour mixture into pan on top of crumbs.
Place strawberries on top of mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over strawberries and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir by hand. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a preheated 325 degree oven until glassy and set out for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients; press into a 9-inch pie plate, bottom and sides.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole with bacon.
Add rice; sprinkle with seasoning packet.
Put chicken pieces on rice and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Drain mushrooms and reserve juice.
Pour mushrooms on chicken and sprinkle with oregano.
Cover all with cream of chicken soup.
Use mushroom juice and add water to fill 4 ounce can; pour over all.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover with foil; seal tightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chery's poppy seed bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in large bowl, flour, sugar and baking soda.
In saucepan, mix 2 sticks oleo, 6 tablespoons chocolate syrup and water.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
In large measuring cup, beat (with fork) eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture to flour mixture and stir in eggs, etc.
No need for electric mixer.
A big spoon is fine.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: coffee roast
directions: Cut slits completely through brisket.
Insert garlic and onion.
Pour vinegar over the meat, working into slits. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Pre-heat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and 1/3 C. oil.
Put 1/3 C. oil in an iron skillet.
Heat skillet for several minutes in oven.
Pour half of mixture into skillet; sprinkle on half of cheese.
Pour remaining batter into skillet, and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until tooth pick comes out clean.

title: queen mother cake
directions: Melt chocolate with butter; stir until smooth.
Grind almonds with 1/4 cup sugar in blender.
Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until thick.
Add chocolate and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold into chocolate mixture.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: potatoes and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and set aside. Mix cream cheese, milk, Swiss cheese, Cheddar cheese and margarine. Add hash browns. Put half cheese mixture in baking dish. Add broccoli and then remaining cheese mixture. Put bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese logs
directions: Whip butter in electric mixer 2 minutes, adding hot water gradually.
Add flour, mixing to make soft dough.
Stir in cheese and curry.
Chill until stiff enough to handle.
On floured board, roll dough into logs 1/2-inch in diameter, cut into 2-inch pieces. Brush with beaten egg, roll in sesame or poppy seed and place 1-inch apart on greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until firm.

title: imperial crab
directions: Cook onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour. Add milk and cook until thick.
Add seasonings, eggs, then crabmeat.
Place in 6 well-greased 5 ounce cups.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter; pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down.

title: simple lasagna
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
Cook hamburger.
Then mix with sauce. Add oregano to sauce.
Use a 10 x 6-inch greased baking dish.
Make layers of ingredients:
half the noodles, half the cottage cheese, half the Mozzarella and half the sauce.
Repeat with remaining amounts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice, salt and water into a heavy saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until water boils.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and raisins; add slightly beaten eggs gradually while beating into rice mixture.
Return to low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats large metal spoon.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nutmeg.
Serve hot or cold.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add ingredients.
Place in cooking dish in oven.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top; bake for 20 minutes.

title: spicy raspberry cake
directions: Gently rinse berries; pat dry and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Put 1 cup only of the berries in a blender and puree, then stir the pureed berries and juice, along with the 3 remaining cups whole berries, into butter-sugar-egg mixture.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot over medium-high heat.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Add gravy, milk and broccoli; heat slowly, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring frequently, just until cheese is melted. Serve.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon until crispy and reserve drippings.
Add onion and saute until clear.
Add flour to form paste.
Cook until golden brown.
Add liquid from potatoes and stir.
Add potatoes, corn and white pepper.

Cook until desired thickness. Good right out of the pot or warmed up several days later, even better later. May use fresh potatoes, especially leftover baked potatoes, but the canned ones are pretty good and easy.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix.
Bake as you would cornbread, maybe a little longer. CORNBREAD, CORN MUFFINS, OR CORNSTICKS

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Mix
well.
Divide
in 4 patties.
Flatten as you would hamburger
patties.
Then
cup your hands around the patty and at the
same
time,
turn in circular motion and push sides of patty inward.
Flip
patty
over, cup your hands around patty and repeat the procedure.
Pat the patty down as you go if it becomes
too thick.
Repeat about half a dozen times or until you have
a
very firm patty about 3 inches in diameter and 1 1/2-inches
thick. Wrap
piece of bacon around each patty. Secure
with toothpick.
Broil
as
you
would
your favorite steak.

title: french coffee
directions: Pour 1 to 1 1/2-inches of condensed milk into heatproof drinking glass.
Fill heatproof drinking glass 3/4 full with coffee.
Stir until milk is dissolved in coffee.
Add ice cubes. Makes a quick cold dessert drink.

title: buttermilk-pecan chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and dredge in flour mixture, coating well.
Place in baking dish, turning once to coat with butter.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yields 8 servings.
Invite the neighbors over!

title: creamy chicken and bows
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and stir in chicken with red pepper.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add green onion, bell pepper, cheese, garlic powder and Cup-a-Soup blended with milk.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Toss with hot pasta bows.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, squeeze dry.
Mix remaining ingredients and roll in balls.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put all ingredients, including oyster stock, in large pot. Heat on medium-low until hot and margarine has melted.
Stir frequently.
Do not allow stew to boil.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: easy fajitas
directions: Saute meat, peppers and onions in Italian dressing.
Warm tortillas in a frying pan.
Wrap meat mixture in tortilla along with cheese, sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes (per taste).

title: greek cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
I use a 10-inch iron skillet to bake this in.

title: italian ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla in one bowl.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, then flour lightly.
Put cake mix on bottom.
Pour cheese mixture gently on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check after 45 minutes. If cake springs back, it's done.

title: pronto pinto chips
directions: In small dish, mash beans with fork.
Mix in salsa and sour cream.
Serve as dip with chips.
Makes 1 serving, 260 calories, 1.5 grams fat and 1.9 grams soluble fiber.
This is a heart smart snack.
Low in fat, high in fiber.

title: snickerdoodles coffee cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, milk, margarine and egg.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top heavily with sugar (this gives a crusty top).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mayonnaise bread
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise in mixing bowl.
Add milk, a small amount at a time, mixing well.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes six muffins.
They are like rolls.

title: cole slaw
directions: In a small bowl,
mix
together
the
vegetable oil and vinegar, lemon or lime
juice.
Then add the prepared mustard, celery salt, mayonnaise,
salt,
pepper and paprika.
Mix well and pour over the shredded cabbage and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need 1 plastic shovel and 1 plastic flowerpot, 8-inch diameter.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish and press to form bottom layer.
Cream sugar, eggs, softened butter and vanilla in mixer bowl for 15 minutes.
Spread filling over crust.
Arrange bananas over mixture.
Spoon pineapple evenly over bananas and sprinkle with the coconut. Layer topping, cherries and nuts over top.
Chill.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Grease 9 x 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and line with waxed paper. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, mix nuts, dates and cherries.
Sift flour mixture over fruit and nut mixture.
Mix with hands until nuts and fruits are well coated.
Beat 3 eggs until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Pour over other mixture and blend well.
Put into pan, packing evenly.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Combine milk and eggs, add to flour and beat well with rotary egg beater until smooth.
Pour hot drippings into hot shallow pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Pour in mixture quickly and bake in hot oven (400°) for 1/2 hour.
The pudding may then be placed under the rack holding the roast beef and left for 15 minutes to catch the juices from the roast.
If a rack is not used, cut pudding into squares and arrange in pan around roast. Serve with the meat.

title: summer squash casserole cockaigne
directions: Cut the summer squash into small pieces.
Simmer, covered, until tender, about 6 to 8 minutes, in a small amount of boiling water.
Shake the pan to keep from sticking; drain well.
Combine sour cream, butter, grated cheese, salt and paprika.
Stir this mixture over low heat until the cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the beaten egg yolk and chopped chives.
Add the squash.
Put the mixture in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover the top with dry bread crumbs, dots of butter and grated cheese. Brown in a preheated 375° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: deviled cream cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Makes about 1 cup. Good filling for celery sticks or spread on crackers.

title: rum raisin dip
directions: Soak raisins in rum for 10 min.
Pour off rum, mix cream cheese with sugar until smooth.
Add raisins, chocolate chips and nuts. Serve with gingersnaps.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add soups (no water) and stir to blend.
Top with 1 box prepared stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Pour half and half into a large bowl.
Add pie filling mix. Beat with wire whisk until well blended 1 minute. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice. Spoon in crust.

title: heavenly bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When slightly cool, spread with melted chocolate and sprinkle with nuts or colored sprinkles.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs with oil.
Stir in sugar, zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
Sift in flour, bran, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend remaining ingredients into zucchini mixture, adding nuts last.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until it tests done.

title: glorious morning muffins(makes 30 muffins)
directions: Sift together, in a large bowl, flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apples.
In another bowl, whisk together eggs, oil and vanilla until mixed. Add to flour mixture.
Stir just to combine.
Fill to top of muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey pate
directions: Grind walnuts in food processor.
Add remaining pate ingredients.
Process until finely ground.
Cover and chill at least 1 or up to 24 hours.
Makes 3 cups, 20 calories per teaspoon.
Serve with crackers or crudites.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm by placing cup in hot water.
Dissolve yeast in milk.
Mix dry ingredients; blend in Crisco, then buttermilk.
Roll on floured board until 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter or Crisco.
Cut and place on greased pan, then place another layer on top.
Cover and rise 1 1/2 hours or until double in size.
Bake in 400° to 500° oven for 20 minutes or more.

title: champagne cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat pudding and milk together until thick.
Add cream cheese which has been beaten until smooth. Blend well.
Spread on top of cake.
Next, spread crushed pineapple, which has been drained overnight, over pudding.
On top of this, spread Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Measure together buttermilk, oil and egg.
Blend together wet and dry ingredients.
Mix just until mixture is damp.
Bake on a medium hot griddle.
Flip when cakes are bubbly around the edge.

title: complete healthy meal
directions: Season chicken parts with Mrs. Dash salt free seasoning. Place in a baking dish.
Add a little water.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until well cooked.
Place Success boil-a-bag in boiling water for 10 minutes (no butter).
Steam broccoli to desired tenderness.

title: oatmeal pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch pie shell (uncooked).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: party nibbles
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large roasting pan. Stir well. Combine the next 3 ingredients and stir well. Drizzle over nut mixture. Stir well. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Makes 3 quarts.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and peel eggplant and slice thin.
Fry in peanut oil until soft.
Drain on paper towels.
Place some sauce on bottom of baking dish.
Layer noodles, sauce, eggplant, cheeses.
Continue layers, ending with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Spray with Pam.
Bake until bubbly at 350°. Also can add shredded Cheddar cheese on top last 5 minutes.

title: chicken crepes
directions: In a saucepan, cook celery and onion with seasoning in butter until tender.
Add 1/2 c. soup and chicken.
Heat, stirring often. Spoon onto crepes. Roll up.
Keep warm.
Add remaining soup and milk to saucepan.
Heat.
Stir often.
Pepper to taste.
Place crepes on a serving dish and spoon sauce over them.

title: buns(makes 2 dozen plus)
directions: In large bowl, mix yeast and lukewarm water.
Add and beat 2 cups flour, then add sugar, oil, eggs and salt.
Then add 4 1/2 cups flour (or more).
Knead and cover.
Let rise 1 hour.

title: country style cole slaw
directions: Stir together and mix with the following:

title: tipsy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Lower heat and simmer for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Recipe can be doubled and baked at 300° in the oven.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the fat. Saute onion several minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Heat thoroughly. Pour into serving dish. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Serves 8.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Cook roast until tender.
Set aside and shred.
Brown butter and onions.
Add garlic, celery, mustard and water.
Cook a few minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add shredded meat.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up broccoli and cauliflower (raw).
Make sauce out of vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour sauce over vegetables; refrigerate for 6 hours.
Add raisins; top with bacon pieces or Bac*Os right before serving.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Heat 2 cups fruit juice and water to boiling point.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Fold into gelatin mixture. Chill for several hours.

title: louisa's pilaf
directions: Brown
vermicelli in butter.
Mix in rice and bouillon. Cook in casserole 30 to 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: new orleans jambalaya
directions: Put pork chops in frying pan or skillet.
Put on high heat. Go away and do not tend for at least 30 minutes.
When you return, fan smoke detector as it should be blaring by now.
Scrape or chisel pork chops from pan and either throw away or use as hockey pucks.
Send out for pizza!

title: stove top chicken
directions: Boil chickens in water with onion, celery, salt and pepper. Save 1 3/4 C of strained broth.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Ten minutes before cake is done, melt 1 stick butter, 1 cup sugar and 2 small cans Pet milk and bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Take cake out of oven and pour on cake while hot.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add cold water; partly congeal.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Add cream cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rum cake
directions: Line bottom of Bundt pan with margarine, pecans and brown sugar.
Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, rum and water together.
Pour over pecan mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn out at once on plate.

title: pam's carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onion, potato and carrots.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add stock and sugar.
Boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Puree in blender.
Return to pan and stir in half and half and heat (do not boil).

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Cool and debone.
Crush the crackers and mix well with margarine.
Cover bottom of baking dish with cracker mixture.
Layer chicken on top of crackers.
Mix sour cream, soup and chicken broth; pour over chicken and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Last 10 minutes, add cheese.

title: cheesy noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix grated cheese, cottage cheese and beaten eggs together.
Add salt if the cheese is not salty enough already.
Divide into two equal portions; combine parsley with one half.
Place half of the drained noodles in a buttered flat baking pan.
Add the cheese with parsley, the rest of the noodles and then the remaining cheese mixture.
Dot with butter and bake in a 350° oven until browned, approximately 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grate orange peel of one orange.
Juice the oranges.
Put peel, juice, apples and cranberries in blender and blend until coarse.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar.
Add the nuts just before serving.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and refrigerate.
It's better the 2nd day.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine in saucepan the soy sauce, brown sugar, water, garlic powder, ginger and vinegar.
Heat through to melt brown sugar.
Do not boil.

title: ring of plenty
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch ring molds.
Set in pan of water (1-inch deep).
Bake until set, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Unmold on hot platter.
Fill center with creamed seafood, chicken or vegetable.
Yields 8 servings.

title: almond caramel bars
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, eggs, sugar, 1/2 cup almonds and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Spread mixture into a buttered 9-inch square pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove tough stems from spinach and rinse to remove grit. Tear spinach into bite sized pieces.
Put into salad bowl.
Chop hard-boiled eggs and slice onion.
Add to salad bowl.
Add bacon bits and toss.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Let stand for 24 hours. (Chickpeas may be used, also.)

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Bring 1 cup of water to a boil; stir in jello until dissolved. Add remaining 1/2 cup water and juice.
Gradually add jello to cream cheese, mixing until blended.
Chill until thickened, but not set.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix crumbs and butter. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Place rest of ingredients in layers as listed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into small squares.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Make the Jiffy cake as directed and spread in 9 x 13 pan. Cool.
(Bake 14 to 15 minutes; check cake.)
Drain pineapple well and set aside.
Beat the softened cream cheese with milk.
When smooth, add the pudding and mix until thick.
Spread this mixture on cooled cake.
Then spread pineapple and last, top with Cool Whip.
You can garnish with nuts, coconut or cherries.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel peaches, wash, drain or open can of peaches.
Place into mixing bowl.
Combine sugar and flour.
Be sure to pour juice from peach can.
Place cobbler mixture in a casserole dish (spray dish with Pam).
Bake at 350° until crust appears brown.

title: crabcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs. Shape into round cakes about 1-inch thick. Coat with bread crumbs and deep fry (or broil) to golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and add cornbread mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: president truman's crustless apple pie
directions: Butter a pie dish well and fill with apples.
Add brown sugar, dot with butter and flavor with cinnamon, salt and nutmeats (optional).
Sift flour with baking powder.
Sprinkle over mixture and through apples.
Add 1/2 cup of water and bake.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Spray Pam in baking dish.
Dunk chicken breasts in milk and coat with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Easy and low calorie.

title: meatballs in wine sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except the butter; shape into balls the size of walnut.
Brown in butter, turning often to retain shape. Set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, dry ingredients and apples.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350°.
Serve while warm with a sauce or whipped cream.

title: grilled duck
directions: Marinate duck breasts in Zesty Italian for approximately 6 hours.
Rinse and wrap ducks with raw bacon, using a toothpick to hold in place.
Grill.
Serve with rice mixture:
Mix uncooked rice with consomme, mushrooms and margarine and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pillsbury lemon cake
directions: Mix and follow directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured lightly.
Bake at 350°.
When done, remove from oven and, with a large fork, put holes throughout cake.
When cool, pour the crushed pineapple (juice and all) on cake.

title: barb's potato salad
directions: Wash and halve red potatoes.
Cook in salted water until fork starts to pierce potatoes.
Add 3 eggs and boil with potatoes.
In 4 minutes, remove from heat and drain.
When cool, peel potatoes and eggs.
Chop onion up finely.
Dice cucumber and pepper, if wanted. Drain can of peas and put all together in a large bowl. Spread 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper, then mix thoroughly.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Then add salad dressing and mix again.
This allows flavors to blend.

title: coconut and walnut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil.
Beat 4 minutes at medium.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.
Use remaining coconut and spread on cake.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie shell until brown.
Cool. Chop one cup of strawberries.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually until smooth.
Add chopped berries.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring. Cool in refrigerator 1/2 hour.

title: grandmother's divinity
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Then cook over low heat without stirring until hard ball is formed (265°).
Test.
Put into another bowl the egg whites and salt.
Beat egg whites, then add to other mixture. Add nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt together.
Pour over other ingredients and marinate at least 12 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: strawberry-pineapple delight
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours to thicken and set.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: oat raisin cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat margarine until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in cereal and raisins. Drop by level tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheets.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and flour to make dough.
Cook dates with 1 cup water, stirring until thick, to make filling.
Add nuts and sugar to date mixture.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place filling on circle.
Fold in half and seal with fork.
Dip in sugar.
Bake on middle shelf for 20 minutes.

title: deep dish chili pie
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef in oil; drain fat.
Add stewed tomatoes, bell pepper, taco spices and seasonings and cornmeal. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Add kidney beans.
In a 10-inch pie plate, unfold one crust and fill with chili mixture and 1/4 cup cheese.
Top with remaining crust and flute edges.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over crust, return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh peach pudding
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
In a large shallow dish, layer vanilla wafers; top with peach mixture.
Continue layering until peach mixture is used, starting with wafers and ending with wafers.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cream the shortening and brown sugar.
Sift dry ingredients. Add with milk.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in a 350° oven until it starts to leave sides of pan.
Makes a large cake.

title: italian rice salad
directions: Toss with Italian salad dressing.
Chill well.

title: popover pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown beef with onion. Drain grease off. Stir in sauce mix, tomato sauce and water; simmer 10 minutes. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and top with Mozzarella cheese. Beat eggs, milk and oil until foamy.
Beat in flour and salt until batter is smooth; pour over meat. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Cut into squares.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: In a casserole dish, put enough rice to serve your family and add just enough water to cover rice.
Dot with butter.
Add a little salt.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture and cover with cream of chicken soup.
Cover casserole dish with aluminum foil and cook 1 hour at 350°.
You have chicken, rice and gravy.

title: butterflied leg of lamb
directions: Combine soy sauce, wine, garlic, rosemary and pepper.
In a shallow baking pan, marinate the lamb at least 6 hours in the marinade; refrigerate, turning often.

title: beef burgundy barbecue
directions: In glass bowl or shallow dish, combine all ingredients, except meat and green pepper.
Add beef.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour or refrigerate overnight (which is better to add flavor and tenderize the meat).

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in large greased casserole dish.

title: baby food plum cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil and eggs; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add plums, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pepper steak and dip in flour, coating both sides.
Place in large crock-pot.
Add soup mix, potatoes and carrot.
Cover all with water to rim of crock-pot. Cook, covered, on medium for 3 hours or until steak is done. Soup and flour forms a gravy.

title: hungarian chicken paprikosh
directions: Saute onions, garlic and chicken until onions are translucent and chicken is lightly browned.
Boil water in a large pot.
After boiled, put the onions, garlic and chicken into pot.
Reduce heat; simmer for 2 hours.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Saute onions and peppers in 1/4 cup butter until tender. Remove from heat and add chicken. Soften tortillas in hot oil 2 to 3 minutes on each side; drain. Spoon chicken mixture onto each tortilla; add small amount of Cheddar cheese to each and roll up. Place seam side down in casserole sprayed with cooking spray. Melt remaining butter over medium heat. Stir in flour, cooking until smooth. Gently stir in chicken broth. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in sour cream. Pour over enchiladas. Top with Monterey Jack cheese. Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix together the pineapple, flour, eggs, vanilla, sugar, pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening, add to sugar.
Add beaten egg to mixture. Add milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add.
Add raisins that have been dusted with flour.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate ribbon pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon milk in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread onto bottom of prepared crust.
Pour 2 cups of milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set. Just before serving, spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Garnish with shaved chocolate, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gram schrauder's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and nutmeg.
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Drop from spoon onto greased pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 12 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: spinach pasta primavera
directions: Thinly slice yellow squash, zucchini squash, red bell pepper, carrot and green chili pepper.
Cook fettuccine 10 minutes in boiling, salted water or to desired texture.
Drain and wash under cold water.

title: springtime salad
directions: Put sour cream in bowl with ingredients, except coconut.
Mix together.
Fold in coconut.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: paula's trail mix
directions: In a large container with a tightly sealed lid mix all ingredients except oil.
Pour oil over this, seal and shake well. This can also be done in a large bowl and mixed with a spoon. Spread on a cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Stir several times while baking.
Cool and place in plastic bag.
These are good to have on hand in the freezer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put sugar in medium sized bowl, add softened margarine, blend, add syrup and well beaten eggs.
Mix well by hand (do not use electric mixer).
Add pecans and pour in partially cooked pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Reduce to 200° and bake for 1 hour.
The slow baking keeps the nuts from getting too hard.
For 2 regular crust pies use 1 and 1/2 recipe.
My son-in-law says this is the best pecan pie ever!!

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Mix in eggs, salt and soda. Add flour.
Mix well and add walnuts.
Spoon out on wax paper, making 3 or 4 rolls.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° until done.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken in orange curry sauce
directions: Cook chicken in oil until slightly browned. Set aside.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until marmalade is melted and sauce bubbles. Turn chicken in sauce to coat.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack in 5 hot, sterilized pint jars.
Put 1 pepper and 1 garlic clove in each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour over okra and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: make ahead creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with 1 teaspoon salt until tender.
(Peel if desired.)
Drain well.
Mash potatoes with masher until smooth. Add cream cheese, 4 tablespoons butter, garlic salt, pepper and remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add heavy cream, mixing until smooth.
Turn potato mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Bake at once or refrigerate overnight.)
Dot top of potatoes with 2 tablespoons butter and paprika.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes; increase to 375° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop up lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
After browning ground beef, mix all ingredients together.
(Crunch up Doritos chips before mixing.)
Chill.

title: tuna dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with chips, crackers or fresh vegetable dippers.

title: cake mix rolls
directions: Beat water and yeast.
Add 1 cup flour and beat.
Add salt, cake mix and 4 cups flour.
Stir with spoon.
Raise in greased bowl.
Raise 1 time.
Punch down.
Form balls and put in greased pan.
Raise about 40 minutes or until doubled in size about.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cover with towel while raising.

title: maple sugar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool.
Put in a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Very rich.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide dough into 4 sections and refrigerate.
Roll and cut with small round cutter or glass.
Bake in electric frying pan at 300° for 4 minutes on each side. Sprinkle with sugar.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: covered chicken dish
directions: Take the pieces of chicken; sprinkle Lawry's salt and pepper on each one.
Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the 3 cans of soup together; then pour over chicken.
Cook in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cook with pan, covered.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a small amount of oil, brown your chicken on both sides (only takes a short time).
Blend soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Drain oil from skillet.
Pour all of soup mixture over chicken.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Turn occasionally if needed.
Prepare your rice (I use Success rice).
Put chicken and gravy over rice and serve.

title: quick and easy frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour on very low heat; stir continually.
Stir until it becomes like pudding.
Cool water.
Beat sugar and Crisco at high speed until fluffy, then beat all together.
Put in teaspoon of vanilla; beat until fluffy and tastes good.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth. Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy kiss, covering completely. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: old el paso mexicali casserole
directions: Remove wrappers from tamales; cut tamales in thirds and 6 inches half diagonally. Mix in 1 1/2-quart casserole the tamales (cut in thirds), corn, sausages and soup. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Top casserole with remaining tamales and cheese. Heat until cheese melts.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Grease shallow baking pan or loaf pan.
Directions for Cuisinart:
Chop onion and parsley 30 seconds.
Add bread, tarragon, chicken broth, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, rosemary and egg.
Pulse 60 seconds.
Add turkey.
Pulse gently just to fold in.
Mold and shape into a loaf.
Put in pan, dot with margarine.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes. Pour tomato sauce over meat, add oregano and bake 20 minutes more.
Serves 4. Can be done by hand.
Break up bread and chop onion first.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples; remove stems.
Insert craft sticks into stem end of each apple; set aside.
Combine caramels, vanilla, and 1 tablespoon water in a microwave-safe glass bowl.
Microwave on HIGH 90 seconds or until melted, stirring twice.
Dip each apple into the caramel mixture quickly, allowing excess caramel to drip off.
Roll in chopped pecans; place on lightly greased wax paper. Chill at least 15 minutes.
Microwave chocolate morsels at HIGH 90 seconds or until melted, stirring twice; cool 5 minutes.
Pour chocolate where craft sticks and apple meet, allowing chocolate to drip down sides of apples.
Press pecan halves onto chocolate, if desired.
Chill 15 minutes or until set.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine sour cream, soup and poppy seeds in a bowl; stir in chicken.
Pour into greased 13x9 baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through.
May be served alone or over rice. Serves four.

title: cold fruit delight
directions: Put all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch dish and mix good.
Put in freezer for at least 6 hours.
Before serving, let set out for 15 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake 1 tablespoon flour inside large cooking bag.
Place ham inside bag after you have trimmed excess fat away and rinsed ham in water.
Use the juice and pulp from the orange and mix with the water and brown sugar.
Pour mixture over ham.
Bake as bag instructions indicate for the weight of the ham plus about 30 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In saucepan, heat water and sugar until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll dough into a large rectangle, about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples and stir. Sprinkle apples evenly over dough and roll up like a jelly roll. Slice 1/2 inch thick and place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around apple rolls.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk; bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and the macaroni.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 4 quart club aluminum or cast iron pot, brown ground beef (crumbled).
Drain and chop mushrooms, medium fine, and boil separately for about 45 minutes and drain.
Add all ingredients to ground beef and let simmer 2 hours or longer.
Stir often.

title: choc-lush dessert
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and butter well and press in glass baking dish (7 x 11 or 8 x 10-inches).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Be careful not to burn it.)
Cool.
Spread with whipped topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take bone out.
Tear into small pieces.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs.
Put half of crumbs in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken soup and 2 cans of broth, where chicken was cooked, to chicken and stir.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Bake until brown at 375°.

title: lemon sponge pie or baking dish
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add lemon juice and rind, egg yolks and flour.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to lemon mixture.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve slightly cooled or room temperature.

title: crab casserole
directions: Dilute soup with 1 soup can milk.
Don't mix soup and meat together.
Layer soup and crabmeat in a greased oblong baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated and hot.
Kids love it.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Beat lemonade and condensed milk together and fold into Cool Whip.
Turn into pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Really good pie!
Makes 8 servings.

title: icebox cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in double boiler.
Roll crackers real fine.
Add mix of nuts and fruit to the crackers. Pour marshmallow mixture over crackers and fruit and work up good with hands and place in buttered pan.
Press good into pan.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
To take out of pan, place pan over a burner for a few seconds and turn upside down on a cloth and the cake will slide out of pan.

title: frogmore stew
directions: In large stock pot, bring water and Old Bay seasoning to a boil.
Add potatoes; cook for 15 minutes.
Add sausage and cook 5 minutes more.
Add corn; cook another 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp; cook until shrimp are pink.
Drain immediately and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: white sauce for vegetables
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and salt. Stir until smooth.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.

title: chop suey
directions: Lightly brown cubed steak.
Then simmer onion a bit.
Fry bacon and use 2 tablespoons fat.
Then add quart of tomato, celery, cabbage, rice, sauce, paprika, salt and pepper.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: bambinos
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spread crackers with catsup and top with pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in the last 6 ingredients for 3 to 4 hours. Bake for 45 minutes at 325° or until brown.
Delicious for calorie counters.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toast coconut. Set aside.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch container.
Chill until firm.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Boil, pour over cabbage mixture and chill 4 hours.

title: date nut bread
directions: Scald dates; sprinkle dates with baking soda.
Add butter; let cool and set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, salt and flour; beat together.
Add chopped nuts.
Add date mixture; beat.
Fold in 2 egg whites (stiffly beaten); bake in a slow oven (225° to 250°) for 1 hour.
Makes 2 (8 1/2 x 2 x 4-inch) loaves or 1 (13 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch) loaf.

title: baklava
directions: Mix together walnuts, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Brush appropriate size glass pan (11 x 14-inch) with melted butter. Layer 1/4 phyllo sheets 1 by 1 brushing with butter between each sheet. Add 1/3 nut mixture. Repeat with phyllo, creating 2 more layers. Top with remaining 1/4 of phyllo sheets. Cut into diamonds; pour any remaining butter over the top. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°. Remove and cool slightly (5 minutes).

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk in a double boiler.
Break up bread, pressing gently until cup is full. Add milk with butter and sugar and let stand until cool. Add egg, flavoring and salt.
Place in greased baking dish and bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.
Make meringue, if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Add together all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 325° in oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes in slightly greased small muffin pan or bake at lower temperature at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directions call for.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch round pans greased and floured.
Cook until done.
Cool completely.

title: oven "fried" salmon cakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Shape into eight 1/2-inch patties.
Place on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet and bake 10 or 12 minutes at 400°, turning once, until golden on both sides.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cold melon soup
directions: Finely chop 1 1/2 cups of honeydew and cantaloupe and set aside.
Place remaining melon, orange juice, lime juice and honey in blender and puree for a few seconds.
Pour into a large bowl; stir in champagne and reserved melon.
Cover and refrigerate. Garnish when serving with whipped cream (a dollop per bowl) and mint leaves.
Good soup for company.
Very refreshing on a hot day. Serves 6 to 8.

title: grapefruit banana energizer
directions: Peel grapefruit; remove seeds and cut in chunks.
Peel banana and slice.
Place grapefruit and banana with fructose in blender. Blend until smooth.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the middle of mixture.
Set aside.
Combine orange juice and next four ingredients.
Stir well.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moist.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Divide batter evenly into coated muffin pans.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake for approximately 18 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: soft cutout sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar and butter flavor Crisco.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add gradually in 1/4's to cream mixture.
Chill.
Put flour (1 teaspoon) on wax paper.
Flatten and turn over dough and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 9 minutes, depending on size.
Do not overbake.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole using microwave. Blend in the flour; add chicken broth and milk.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes or until thick, stirring every minute.
Add remaining ingredients and continue to cook 4 minutes or until hot enough to serve.
Stir in grated cheese.
Serve over toast, biscuits or in patty shells.

title: linguini and clams
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
While pasta cooks, prepare sauce in medium size saucepan.
Heat oil over moderate heat.
Add garlic and when golden brown, add drained clam juice, wine, oregano and pepper.
Simmer gently over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in clams and parsley and cook until heated through.
Put hot cooked, drained pasta into serving bowls and ladle hot sauce over it.

title: what's for supper?(beans and hamburg)
directions: Brown meat.
Add chopped, small onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Don't forget the pickles.
Any of these ingredients can be varied to suit taste.
A meat stretcher if needed.
Add more beans.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs, then coconut, chips and nuts.
Pour milk over top evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir cream cheese and sour cream until blended.
Stir in soup mix, artichokes, shrimp, red pepper and hot pepper sauce until well mixed.
Spoon into 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, water and butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boiling.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Cool and stir in vanilla.

title: tiramisou
directions: Beat egg yolks until frothy.
Add sugar slowly, blending well, until golden yellow.
Add Mascarpone cream cheese, beating in thoroughly.
Sprinkle ladyfingers with coffee-rum mixture. Arrange ladyfingers around sides and bottom of deep glass dish or a 6-cup Charlotte mold.
Beat egg whites until stiff and standing in soft peaks. Gently fold into egg yolk mixture.
Spoon carefully into prepared mold or dish.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Unmold just before serving.
Decorate with fresh raspberries and shaved chocolate.
Chocolate sauce can also be piped on decoratively.
Serves 8.
Enjoy! Nonfattening!
It's all in the mind.

title: dad's potato salad(lawrence wangler)
directions: Boil eggs (do not let eggs overboil) and cool immediately. Peel.
(Eggs have a rubber taste if they are overcooked and ruin the taste of the potato salad.)

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cook over medium-low heat in double boiler.
When chips are melted, add nuts.
Stir.
Put spoonfuls on wax paper covered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Add soup, Veg-All, onion, pepper and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole and add biscuits on top.
Separate biscuits in half.
Bake until brown, according to biscuit instructions.

title: lenten borsht(for holy supper)
directions: Simmer dried mushrooms in water for 1 hour.
Strain through cloth, saving liquid.
Wash mushrooms thoroughly and chop into pieces.
Saute onions in oil until brown.
Add to fry pan, the beets, carrot and celery; cook 5 minutes.
Add this mixture to soup pot of boiling water, bay leaf, onion, salt, pepper, lemon juice and tomato paste.
Simmer 20 minutes; add cabbage, mushrooms, both types, mushroom stock, lima beans and dill.
Let slowly simmer until all added vegetables are done.
Let cool and absorb flavors. Can be reheated and each time it tastes better.

title: applesauce loaf bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, lemon juice, applesauce and then dry ingredients, stirring only enough to dampen all the flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: yellow cake
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients by hand or mixer. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Blend with mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into two 9-inch layer pans that have been rubbed with Crisco and lightly floured. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bark
directions: Line jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) with aluminum foil. Spray with Pam.
Line pan with unsalted saltines.
Cut to fit.
In saucepan, melt butter and brown sugar.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes only (watch, may burn). Push down any crackers that may pop up.
Pour the milk chocolate chips on top and let them melt; then spread like frosting. Refrigerate or freeze.
Break into chunks to serve.

title: john's favorite broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and milk; blend well.
Put rice in bottom of dish; cover with soup mixture and spread broccoli on top.
Cover with shredded Cheddar and Swiss cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef; drain and cool.
Chop lettuce, onion and tomatoes. Crush chips.
Mix together with meat.
Add salt and avocado.
Use Thousand Island dressing (large bottle).
Use a punch bowl to serve it in.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Stir in sauce and soups. Let simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring often.
In a casserole dish, crush Doritos and pour ground beef mixture over the chips. Top with cheese.
Place in oven just long enough for the cheese to melt.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and hot water with pastry blender.
Roll dough or floured pastry cloth very thin.
Cut with pizza cutter into 1-inch strips.
Drop into boiling chicken broth; add salt and black pepper to taste.
Add chopped chicken breasts.
Cook until dumplings are fluffy on medium-low heat.

title: quick and easy goulash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add Ro-Tel and soups.
Cook for few minutes over medium heat.
Stir often.
Crush Doritos and add to mixture.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks; mix well.
Sift flour and soda together; add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Fill and frost with the following icing.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown all meats together in skillet until done; drain off half the fat.
Pour all sauces into large pot.
Crumble meat into sauces.
Add reserved fat.
Add drained mushrooms, diced onion and all spices.
Stir with wire whisk until mixed.
Cover; cook on low heat for 8 hours.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Reheat on low until heated through.
Serve over pasta.

title: el taco burgers
directions: Mix onions, taco seasoning and peppers with meat and divide into 8 patties.
Cook until done.
Top with cheese, sour cream and salsa.
May serve open-faced on Texas toast or on hamburger buns.

title: barbecue fish steak
directions: Place fish in a shallow baking dish.
Combine oil and lemon juice; pour over fish.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Thoroughly oil, or coat with nonstick spray, a clean, hand-held, hinged grill.
Place fish or steaks on grill and cover.
Cook fairly close to medium hot coals.
Fish must be cooked quickly to prevent its drying out.
The timing is important, too.
Fish is done when it looks opaque.
Do not flip it back and forth while cooking. Cook one side first and then the other.
As a rule of thumb, a 3/4-inch steak will cook in 3 or 4 minutes per side.
Open the grill carefully, loosening any skin that might have become stuck.

title: ham and corn fritters
directions: Combine flour
with baking powder, milk and eggs.
Stir in corn,
ham,
onion and pepper.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil. Fry 3 to 4 minutes on each side until golden.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In a cake pan, combine all ingredients and 3/4 cup cheese, except stuffing and butter.
Toss stuffing mix with butter. Spoon over vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add enough flour until dough is stiff enough to roll out.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Drop in hot lard.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients in 10-inch casserole, putting cheese and potato chips on top.
Cook at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown the chicken.
Put in a loaf cake pan.
Mix water with soup.
Pour on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter. Mix on low speed until blended. Spoon into pie crust and chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Shred cabbage over margarine.
Sprinkle sugar and salt over cabbage.
Pour milk over this.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes. Add soda.
Stir well. Pour over popped corn and coat evenly.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets. Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Separate into pieces while still warm.
Store in airtight containers.

title: easy blueberry muffins
directions: Dredge blueberries in 2 tablespoons flour.
Combine remaining 2 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat together milk, egg and oil; add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened. Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pan two-thirds full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Yields 1 dozen.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix
ingredients
and pour into loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This recipe makes 2 loaves.

title: hearty turkey stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut turkey breast crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Heat oil in 6-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, until oil sizzles, about one minute.
Place turkey, potatoes, carrots, onion and garlic in pan.
Cook and stir 10 minutes or until turkey is lightly browned.

title: bay seafood seasoning blend
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container.
Use with seafood or chicken.
Yield:
1/4 cup.

title: honey chicken salad(new version)
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients. Whisk together mayonnaise, honey, salt and pepper. Add to chicken mixture, stirring gently until combined. Garnish with additional chopped pecans, if desired.

title: pralines
directions: Cook all except pecans to a soft boil.
Let set, then stir by hand.
Mix will start to lose its gloss.
Add pecans and drop on waxed paper.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and set aside.
Using large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and pepper.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Stir until clear and thickened (about 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes; stir gently.
Serve over bed of rice. Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine milk, sugar, and chocolate morsels in a heavy saucepan.
Boil for about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat for about 1 minute. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine water and yeast in a large bowl and let sit for 5 minutes.
Put in the sugar, salt and oil; mix well.
Add 2 1/2 cups of flour; mix well.
Add 2 cups and mix until stiff.
Use last 1/2 cup to put on board and knead dough for awhile (a few minutes). Put into bowl and cover with a clean cloth.
I put into gas oven with only pilot light on to raise for 30 minutes (or warm place). Put onto 3 (12-inch) greased pans.
Add your favorite toppings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, onion and carrots in bowl.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix with mayonnaise and serve.

title: baked garlic chicken
directions: Place breasts in baking pan and pour melted butter over each breast.
Apply salt, pepper and garlic salt as desired.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Combine all but the Jell-O and bring to a boil.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, stirring to dissolve well.
Raspberries can be used in place of strawberries.

title: sugar free banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix in egg white, apple juice, melted margarine and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Leave in pan for 10 minutes and remove. Cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap overnight so the banana flavor will develop.

title: spanish beef rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion, green pepper, meat and rice.
Stir over high heat until slightly brown.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boil.
Cover tightly and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: coconut thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Cream butter flavor Crisco with sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Combine flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Form into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Beat egg white until slightly frothy.
Dip dough balls into egg white, then roll in coconut.

title: m&m's cake
directions: Mix
dates and 1 teaspoon soda with boiling water, then cool. Cream
oleo, 1 cup sugar, eggs, 1 teaspoon soda, vanilla, walnuts, flour and salt.
Mix in above mixture.
Pour into greased and floured
9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and M&M's on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine with 1/2 cup margarine, salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine corn flakes and remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cut into small pieces.
Crush Doritos chips and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix both soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese in skillet and heat until cheese melts.
Add chicken and macaroni.
Stir until well heated.
Pour over Doritos chips.
Place strips of cheese over top.
Heat in oven at 350° until lightly browned on top.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Chex Mix Topping:
Combine Chex and onion powder.
Stir in margarine and set aside.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Melt margarine; add chopped carrots and onions.
Saute for 10 minutes over low heat, stirring often.
Add potatoes and broth to cover everything.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Put through a blender or sieve.
Dissolve powdered milk in liquid milk; heat and add to carrot mixture to thin consistency of thick cream.
Taste; add salt and pepper to season.
Soup may be served hot or cold. Garnish with carrot curls and fresh parsley.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground round in water, stirring often; drain.
In large pot, combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Cook until tender. Add noodles and continue to cook until noodles are tender.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; blend.
Add flour and salt.
Blend to moisten flour. Spread in a rectangle, about 10 x 15-inch, on a greased cookie sheet or on a nongreased Teflon cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Spread with melted chocolate while hot.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or cake sprinkles if desired.
Cut into small squares while warm.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Melt butter in large pan and slowly cook chicken in the butter.
Remove chicken. Add remaining ingredients to butter mixture to make sauce. Simmer 20 minutes.
In a large flat casserole dish put rice on bottom, then add chicken and sauce on top of rice mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Enjoy.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hash brown-cheese casserole
directions: Place potatoes in colander.
Let stand until completely thawed and excess moisture has drained off.
Combine sour cream, soup and butter.
Mix well.
Add salt, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Blend in potatoes.
Place mixture in shallow 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle buttered cornflake crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, in oven preheated to 350° about 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
(This recipe is at its best when assembled not more than 2 hours before it goes into the oven.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: bacon, cheddar and potato chowder
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork, place on a paper towel in microwave oven and microwave on high 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender, turning potatoes over after 6 minutes of cooking.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Cook bacon in large saucepan until crisp.
Transfer with slotted spoon to paper towel lined plate; set aside.
Cook onion in drippings over medium heat about 8 minutes or until tender. Add flour; cook and stir 30 seconds. Add 4 cups milk, salt and pepper; bring to a simmer.
Cut potatoes in half; scoop flesh into a medium bowl.
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk; mash potatoes well and add to soup.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese until melted.
Ladle into soup bowls; top with reserved bacon and remaining 1/2 cup cheese.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; beat well.
Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Add chocolate to sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour mixture into pie crust and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a large bowl, combine sugar and flour. Add corn syrup, coconut, eggs, pineapple, vanilla and butter. Pour into pie shell. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. (Note: Cover loosely with foil if top browns too quickly.) Cool on wire rack. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: tuna hot rice souffle
directions: Combine meat, vegetables, chopped onion, undiluted soups, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup water.
Put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with dough strips, leaving just a small space between strips.
Place several dollops of margarine on top of dough to add in seasoning and browning.
Bake at 350° until mixture is bubbling and dough is golden brown.
If meat/vegetable mixture appears too thick under crust, add a little more water to edge of pie or between dough strips and let water absorb.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Add no salt to this recipe.
Drain and flake salmon.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sesame cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers in a colander. Set the colander on a plate; sprinkle cucumbers with salt and toss. Let stand for 30 minutes. Rinse and drain well. In a bowl, combine cucumbers with the onions, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, oil, sesame seeds, and cayenne pepper. Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: picante soup
directions: Cook chicken, onion, garlic and olive oil in saucepan over medium heat until the chicken is no longer pink (approximately 5 minutes).
Add all other ingredients but pasta.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for about 12 minutes.
Cook pasta separately and add to soup when ready to dip and serve.

title: cheese straws(appetizer)
directions: Rub butter into the flour.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and blend with eggs.
Knead lightly.
Roll pastry 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips, 2 1/2 x 1/4-inch.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger hash
directions: In large skillet, slowly brown beef.
With slotted spoon, remove beef; set aside.
Add enough oil to make 3 tablespoons. Add potatoes, onions and green pepper.
Cook until onions and potatoes are almost tender.
Stir in meat, salt, sugar and pepper. Heat until vegetables are tender.

title: baked crabmeat pie
