directions: Combine ingredients, except almonds, mixing until blended. Spoon mixture into an 8-inch pie plate. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put milk in bowl.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in another bowl. Dip biscuits in milk and roll in cinnamon mixture.
Lay the biscuits overlapping in Bundt pan.
After one can of biscuits, sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Repeat second layer.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix ingredients in plastic gallon jug and finish filling with water.
Shake good to mix and place in freezer.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cocoa and food coloring.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs.
Add cocoa and food coloring mixture.
Add milk and flour.
Add vinegar and soda mixture.
Makes
3 layers.
Bake at 300° to 325°.

title: chicken wrapped in bacon
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste. Cut bacon strips into 3 pieces and wrap chicken breast. Line large casserole or pan with dried beef strips (at least 1 strip per chicken breast). Place breast on top of beef. Add a little water and bake about 45 minutes at 375°. Mix together sour cream and cream of celery soup and pour over the chicken. Return to oven for an additional 20 minutes.

title: sour cream cake with caramel icing
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco, sugar, add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add sour cream, flavoring, salt, soda and flour.
This makes a large cake.
Can be made in layers or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes for tube pan.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in frying pan until done.
Carefully roll out each biscuit to be able to line muffin cups, overlapping the edges some.
Fill each biscuit cup with cooked mixture and top with more grated cheese.
Bring sides of biscuit to the center and pinch together.
Put in oven and follow cooking instructions on biscuit can.
These may be eaten hot or cold, on a plate or by hand.
Hmmm good!!

title: lemon spinach
directions: Boil the spinach until tender in water to which has been added the sugar.
Drain well.
While warm, add the cream cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Mix well until blended and there are no lumps of cheese.
Add the lemon rind (no juice).
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter and mix it with enough of the bread crumbs to make 1/4-inch topping on the spinach and cream cheese mixture.
Bake uncovered for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place Tater Tots in casserole dish.
Mix soup and mushrooms together and pour over Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots thin.
Slice onion.
Chop green pepper.
Cook and drain carrots.
Combine with onion and green pepper.
Combine other ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables and stir until well mixed.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: butter dumplings
directions: Beat these ingredients together.
Drop batter by spoon into simmering soup.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: pineapple crush cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand. Bake at time and temperature given on box.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store in a jar.
Mix by the teaspoons to taste in a cup of hot water.

title: 3 crust for sweet dough
directions: Mix all together and roll out for crust.
Bake according to pie directions.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Pour onto
greased cookie sheet or directly onto aluminum foil.

title: country fried minute steaks
directions: Melt shortening in 10-inch skillet.
Dip steaks in dressing, then in flour, coating both sides.
Pan-fry in hot shortening over medium-high heat, turning to brown both sides, about 4 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashion pecan pie
directions: Bring syrup to a boil in 1 1/2-quart saucepan; boil gently, uncovered, for 8 minutes and cool 15 minutes. Sprinkle nuts in pie shell. Cream butter; blend in sugar, flour and salt. Add eggs, syrup and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until pie is completely puffed across top and browned. Cool before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix in a 1 1/2-quart bowl, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in dark corn syrup.
Put in eggs, one at a time. Mix milk, pecans and vanilla together.
Pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until firm.

title: lep cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll dough into a rope (like a snake) about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Then flatten with hands.
Cut into 2-inch pieces and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: coconut delight
directions: Blend butter, milk and vanilla.
Sift coconut and sugar together; add nuts.
Stir in milk mixture.
Mix quickly until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cool for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into mixture.
Set on cookie sheet until hard.

title: braised roast beef
directions: Spread mustard over meat.
Sprinkle with rosemary and pepper. Put on rack, fat side up, in heavy (tight lid) pan.
Put in 450° oven, uncovered, to brown.
Turn (do not use fork).
Pour heated wine over meat.
Add carrots and onions.
Cover.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Can add more wine over meat the last hour if needed for tenderness.
When done, can add cooked gravy mix to serve.

title: caramel pecan sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together 6 ounces cream cheese and water in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture reaches 115° to 120°, stirring occasionally.
Stir together hot roll mix and yeast packet in large bowl.
Add cream cheese mixture and egg, mixing until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Cover; let rise in warm place for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining cream cheese, sugar and cinnamon in small bowl at medium speed of mixer until well blended.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion, crackers, pepper, garlic, salt and mushrooms with 1/2 of tomato sauce. Place 1/2 of meat mixture into pan; place cheese in center and cover with remaining meat. Seal sides. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry snow
directions: Crumble angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
In a bowl, blend cream cheese and milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour over crumbled cake.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Spread pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: 1-2-3-4 pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add the soda to the buttermilk and let rise a bit.
Add this alternately with flour and salt. Beat well.
Grease and flour 1 tube pan; bake at 325° until lightly browned or done, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix all the ingredients in the order given.
Press and pat mixture evenly onto an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Do not press too thin. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Ice bars while they are hot.
Cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together. Beat eggs in large bowl.
Slowly add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat slowly.
Stir in zucchini (if frozen and thawed, add the extra juice).
Add flour mixture and nuts if desired.
Makes 2 loaves of bread or about 25 to 26 made in pot pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for loaves.

title: raspberry sorbet
directions: Process 15 to 20 seconds in food processor or blender.
Freeze. Strawberries can be substituted for raspberries.
Great and light to clear palate.

title: stir-fry ginger chicken
directions: In wok or skillet, fry chicken in margarine until cooked throughout, using medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl until cornstarch is dissolved.
Pour over chicken and vegetables; bring to a boil. Cook until vegetables are desired tenderness.

title: chopped shoe peg corn salad
directions: Let stand at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: russian tea 2
directions: Add tea bags to water and boil.
Add cloves and simmer 10 minutes. Add juices and bring to a second boil. Remove from heat and serve immediately. Refrigerate unused portion and microwave per cup as desired.

title: pineapple "thing"
directions: Butter baking dish.
Set oven for 350°.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix sugar, flour and just enough juice to make sugar and flour into a paste.
Add pineapple to mixture.
Melt margarine and add crushed crackers.
Pour over pineapple mixture and bake about 30 minutes.

title: sweet beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put bacon and beef in large heavy skillet.
Stir with fork and break up beef until brown.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into greased casserole, 2-quart size. Top with grated cheese and bake 1 hour.

title: country-style potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or plain.

title: mountain dew cake with icing
directions: Beat eggs; mix in oil. Combine cake mix, gelatin and pudding mix. Add to egg mixture alternately with Mountain Dew, beginning and ending with dry mixes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks; add sweetened condensed milk and lime juice. Beat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: strawberry lovers pie
directions: In saucepan, melt 2 ounces chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly; spread or brush over the bottom and up the sides of pastry shell.
Chill.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over chocolate layer; cover and chill 2 hours.
Arrange strawberries, tips up in crust.
Brush jam over top.
Melt remaining chocolate and pour over top.

title: "mintz" cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Firmly press onto bottom and 1 inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese at high speed with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add condensed milk, peppermint candy and food coloring.
Beat well. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Garnish if desired.
Yield:
One nine-inch cheesecake.

title: sugar-free spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, stir 1 1/2 teaspoons mix into 1 cup hot water.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place a slice of Swiss cheese and ham inside of each chicken breast.
Fold meat together and freeze.
When meat has been frozen, dip in beaten eggs, then batter with flour that has been mixed in with Season-All.
Deep fry until light brown.
Do not cook until cheese comes out.
Place chicken on a sheet pan and bake 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 3 tablespoons butter, in small saucepan, saute onion until tender.
Add 2 cups bread crumbs, sugar, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Layer tomatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with layer of onion-bread mixture. Repeat until all is used, ending with tomatoes.
Combine 1/4 cup crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: avocado dippers
directions: Layer ingredients.
Serve with Tostitos or Doritos.

title: shanghai beef
directions: Saute
beef
in
oil
until browned.
Add cornstarch and stir until
blended.
Stir
in broth, chestnuts, pepper, scallions, soy sauce
and black pepper.
Bring to full boil, stirring frequently.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork and make a hog of yourself.

title: zucchini-carrot casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onions for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Drain and set aside.
Separately mix soup, sour cream and carrots.
Add to zucchini.
In another bowl, mix butter and bread crumbs.
Spread half bread crumbs in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour vegetable mix over this, then add remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 (750 ml) sweet white wine and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion; add salt and pepper.

Prepare cornbread mix according to directions and add cream-style corn. Layer ingredients in greased baking dish, beginning with 1/2 cornbread/corn mixture, 1/2 meat, 1/2 grated cheese and repeat the layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until browned.

title: hot hamburger rice dish
directions: Brown meat and onion. Combine all and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
You can top with Chinese noodles, if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook onion in oil until golden.
Add meat and seasoning. Brown.
Add green beans and soup.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole. Mix mashed potatoes with egg and warm milk.
Spoon potato mounds around edges of meat and vegetable mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Prepare
fettucini
noodles
according to directions on package.
Drain.
In
large skillet over low heat, cook margarine, cream and grated Parmesan cheese.
Cook only for a short time, overcooking will cause mixture to be lumpy.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: vernon's chicken supreme
directions: Cut chicken into parts.
Wash chicken.
Mix all ingredients, brush on chicken parts.
Broil one side for 35 minutes at 375°, then turn heat up to 400° until brown.
Turn chicken over to broil to a crispy brown for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: Take thawed bread dough and roll out thin.
Layer in order, boiled ham, Swiss cheese, hard salami and Provolone.
Lightly cover with prepared spaghetti sauce or pizza sauce.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Bake on baking pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mash eggs and mix with crab meat.
Add other ingredients. Save about 1/4 of butter.
Mix well and put into baking dish. Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs and pour remaining butter over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: luxury frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler, cool.
Mix in oleo.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar; beat until smooth.

title: pierogi lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Prepare instant mashed potatoes for serving of 16.
Butter a 9x13 pan.
Melt margarine and saute onions.
Layer the noodles, mashed potatoes, cheese, margarine and onions in 3 layers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Enjoy!!

title: flounder sauces
directions: Combine chili sauce, ketchup, sweet pickle relish and horseradish.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a soft ball stage. Combine other ingredients in small bowl.
Add hot mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: girdle bustin' cake
directions: Combine
yellow
cake
mix,
1 egg and stick of butter. Press into
x 13-inch pan that has been lightly greased and floured. Mix 3 eggs, box of powdered sugar and softened cream cheese.
Pour over
other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
You can put nuts and coconut on.

title: diet center approved squash casserole
directions: Cook together with 1 teaspoon salt; drain.
Mix together squash and onion.
Add egg, green pepper, onion powder and garlic powder. Crush 6 Wasa crackers, add to the mixture, saving 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Sprinkle top with Diet Center Good-Stuff seasoning.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.
Use a 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Makes 4 servings.
Each would be 1 cooked vegetable and 1 bread serving.

title: tomato soup
directions: Peel tomatoes; seed and chop.
(Place tomatoes in boiling water for about 1 minute, then place in cold water; skins will come right off.)
Remove seeds and squish tomatoes through your fingers.
(I find this much more entertaining than chopping.) Saute onion in butter about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, soda and sage.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Mix milk and flour and add slowly.
Add cream and heat.
Normally we double this recipe.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix in large bowl. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese bubbles. Serve with party rye.

title: twinkies
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
Bake and cool.
In saucepan combine milk and flour.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Cool. In medium bowl, combine sugar, salt, Crisco, oleo and vanilla. Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Add flour mixture; beat again until very fluffy.
Cut cake into layers.
Spread mixture on and put on top layer.
Let stand about 48 hours before serving.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In a glass bowl, put sugar, water and butter.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, until it boils.
Stir every 30 seconds.
Pour into blender with dry milk.
Process until smooth. Refrigerate.
Makes 1 cup.

title: southwestern eggs
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a small bowl; add water and mix until incorporated.
Melt butter in non-stick skillet.
Add ham and saute until slightly browned.
Pour eggs onto ham and cook until slightly set.
Add cheese and salsa, stir to blend in and cover pan.
Cook until eggs are set and cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: white chocolate salties
directions: Combine chocolate and Crisco in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts. Pour chocolate mixture into large mixing bowl.
Stir in pretzels and peanuts.
Spread onto buttered cookie sheet or jelly roll pan. Chill 20 minutes or until firm.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen pieces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla; stir in zucchini. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Stir into first mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: lloyd's peanut butter cashew sundae
directions: In a small bowl, combine corn syrup and peanut butter until blended. Serve over ice cream. Sprinkle with cashews. Yields 4 servings.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Serve at once.
Makes 2 to 3 child size servings.

title: mini muffaletta sandwiches
directions: In a measuring cup, combine mustard, salad dressing and spices.
Mix well.
Slice roll in half and spread each half with 1 tablespoon mixture.
Place lettuce leaf on bottom half of roll. Alternately arrange 1/4 of meat and cheese over lettuce.
Cover with top half of roll.
Repeat for each sandwich.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving, 310 calories; 20 grams protein, 24 grams fat, 4 grams carbohydrates, 61 mg. cholesterol, 1583 mg. sodium.

title: chocolate candy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until 234°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat hard for a full 10 minutes.
Pour into dish.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add berries and stir in by hand.
Grease muffin tins well with butter and grease top surface of pans as well (or cupcake liners).
Pile mix high in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle sugar over tops.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 30 minutes if liners are not used.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add chicken (breast is best).
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spread 1 cup pecans in bottom of each pie crust. Pour mixture over top. Put in cold oven. Turn to 300 degrees. Cook for 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: diabetic-coconut surprise cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are golden brown.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 sections.
Shred and cut into strips.
Fry bacon.
Add cabbage to the fat and cook for a short time.
Add sliced apples, water and caraway seeds.
Simmer until done. Season with vinegar, sugar and salt.
Thicken the cooking liquid with the cornstarch and water.

title: wonton chips
directions: Preheat oven to
Lightly
brush 1 side of wonton skins with liquid
margarine
or
melted
margarine or butter. Cut each skin in half diagonally, forming 24 triangles.
Spray a 15 x 10
x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick coating. Arrange triangles, margarine side up,
in
a
single layer in the pan. Sprinkle with seasoned
salt
or cinnamon sugar lightly.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes
or
until golden brown and crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's delicious lime sweet pickles
directions: Mix 1 pint salt to 1 gallon water (boiling).
Pour over cucumbers until covered.
Let stand 1 week.
Drain off salt water and cover with a solution of 1 tablespoon powdered alum to 1 gallon boiling water.
Do this 3 mornings, changing solution each day.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into a well-greased and lightly floured Bundt
pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli florentine
directions: Remove and discard outer leaves and cut off tough ends of stalks from broccoli.
Split lengthwise heavy stalks over 1/2 inch thick.
Boil 2 inches of water in saucepan and add broccoli.
Cover pan, allowing water to form steam.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Do not overcook.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and water.
Sift flour and salt together, then add in butter mixture.
Add pecans and mix thoroughly.
Using portions the size of walnuts, roll into crescent shaped cookies.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
(Mix will look like cornmeal and these cookies will not rise or turn brown.)

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with juice, 1 cup coconut and eggs in large bowl.
Blend on medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Bring margarine, sugar and milk to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining coconut.
Spoon over hot cake in pan.
Serve warm or cool.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt all ingredients, except frozen potatoes, together on stove.
Pour liquid over frozen potatoes.
Sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy salmagundi
directions: Lightly brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in brown rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Stir in corn and additional water, if needed.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings. Contains 4 grams fat per serving.

title: chocolate sauce(works like hot fudge)
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over moderate heat, stirring.
Add evaporated milk (may substitute whatever milk is available). Boil.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: italian mostaccioli(hot dish)
directions: In large saucepan, brown sausage; pour off fat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add pasta sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss hot cooked mostaccioli with oil to coat (prevents sticking together).
Serve with the meat sauce.

title: fry bread
directions: In pan, heat oil to 360°.
In bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in water; knead dough until no longer sticky. Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Pull off 2-inch balls.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each until in a circle shape (1/4-inch thick).
Pierce circles several times.
Deep fry 2 or 3 at a time (cook 1 to 2 minutes).

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1 cup of pecans. Chill and form into a ball. Roll in extra pecans.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook until tender the onions, carrots and potatoes in water with bouillon. Add soup and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.

title: date and nut pinwheels
directions: Mix and roll dough on wax paper and spread with filling. Roll up like a tootsie roll and chill.
Slice thin.
Bake at 400 degrees for approximately 7 minutes or until done.

title: quick casserole
directions: In skillet, saute beef and onion until beef is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Combine with noodles, sauce, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and salt.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add sifted dry ingredients, then vanilla.
Beat for 15 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(This cake will not rise unless beaten as directed.)

title: easy raisin snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° for metal pan and 325° for glass pan. Grease and dust an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into pan.
Bake for 50 minutes, until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or frost.
Yields 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, fry onion and green pepper until soft.
Add ground meat and brown.
Add tomatoes and heat until it bubbles. Turn off heat; add rice and cover.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Let cheese stand until it is at room temperature.
Crumble and mix with sausage.
Add Bisquick and mix together.
Shape into balls and bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Contains 1 gram fat and 117 calories per cupcake.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: pudding pops
directions: Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into popsicle molds.
Insert sticks or straws. Freeze solid.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring until well blended. Pour into 2 large loaf pans, greased and floured.
Place in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix and put in a casserole dish.
Melt 2 teaspoons butter and pour over top.
May add chopped nuts to batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.
Great with Triscuits.

title: spaghetti
directions: Put it in a pot.
Eat it.

title: seven can soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pot. Heat until bubbly. Enjoy on a cold winter night.

title: green punch
directions: Place sherbet in bottom of punch bowl, pour ginger ale over and stir slightly.
Makes a good St. Patrick's or Christmas drink.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar together; blend in eggs, one at a time; sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk. Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Place zucchini in strainer; sprinkle with salt.
Let drain for 10 minutes; squeeze out moisture.
Combine zucchini with eggs, Parmesan cheese and half of the Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses. Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Spoon over baked zucchini mixture.
Top with remaining cheeses; sprinkle with green pepper.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: veggie burger(weight watchers)
directions: Cook wheat and water 15 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 4 equal patties.
Broil about 5 minutes on each side until brown.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 204 calories.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine soup, water and milk. Stir until smooth.
Stir in noodles and herbs. Bring to a low boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover and continue cooking about 10 minutes or until broccoli is done. Season to taste and add more cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: ranch hand sandwiches
directions: Brown bacon, green pepper and onion in a skillet until bacon is done.
Remove drippings, leaving 1 tablespoon.
Mix eggs with cheese.
Pour over bacon mixture in pan.
Cook over low heat and stir until mixture is cooked.

title: kapusta
directions: Combine ingredients. Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours. Drain.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.

title: quick cranberry baked beans
directions: Combine beans and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cups of gold
directions: Wash sweet potatoes and pierce several times with fork.
Bake in microwave/conventional oven and cook until tender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice the end of each orange so they will set and not wobble.
Hollow out the oranges.
Put sweet potato mixture inside of oranges.
Bake at 350° until well heated.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Empty marshmallows into large bowl.
(You can use regular marshmallows and cut them up into small pieces, or use the small ones).
Add crushed pineapple to the marshmallows.
Allow to set for a few hours, until the marshmallows have absorbed the juices from the pineapple.
Mix.
Add whipped cream.
Mix lightly.
Chill and serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain and add vegetables.
Add 3/4 bottle of salad seasoning.
Add Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Let sit overnight.
Serves 8.

title: blender salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed for 10 seconds or until onion is pureed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Cook potatoes and season with butter; let cool.
Add to them the Crisco, sugar, eggs, salt and cream well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to the lukewarm milk and now add this to mixture.
Put in large bowl and start adding the sifted flour to make stiff dough.
Toss on floured board and knead well.
Put back in large bowl and cover and set aside until doubled in size.
Take out and knead again.

Rub top with melted butter and put in refrigerator all day or all night.	Two hours before use roll out part the size of biscuits, but butter in middle and roll over. Let rise until double in size and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: yule cheer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Garnish as desired. Makes 3 quarts.

title: oven barbecued pot roast(heritage recipe)
directions: Place meat and onion in bowl or pan with lid.
For marinade, in container, combine vinegar, catsup, oil and seasonings.
Seal, shake well.
Pour marinade over meat.
Seal and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours (keeping meat covered).

title: stir-fried shrimp
directions: Combine wine, salt, sesame oil and pepper.
Devein shrimp; rinse and drain.
Heat oil; stir-fry pepper and garlic until fragrant.
Add shrimp and stir-fry briefly, then add wine mixture. Cover and cook over medium heat until shrimp change color (about 2 to 3 minutes).
Sprinkle with green onion and serve.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press dough into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayo and salad dressing mix.
Spread on crust.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: mustard
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Let stand for 8 hours. Beat the eggs into mixture.
Heat over low heat (preferably a double boiler) for 30 minutes.
Cook longer if it needs to thicken more.

title: hawaiian nut pie
directions: Mix together and put into 2 pie shells made of graham crackers.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Then serve chilled.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Form into shapes desirable for your pet. Place on	a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza bubble bread
directions: Separate biscuits; snip each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place in a medium mixing bowl.
Add sauce and toss to coat.
Arrange pieces in a circle on a greased pizza pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes or until golden.

title: stuffed whole cabbage
directions: Remove core from head of cabbage; cut out the inside, leaving a hollow shell.
(Save center for use in slaw, etc.)
Soak crumbs in milk and water; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill cabbage with meat mixture and tie it up in a piece of cheesecloth. Put cabbage in large pot of boiling, salted water; boil for 25 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve with tomato sauce, if desired. A chopped green pepper may be added to mixture.

title: country style potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Let chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bohemien coffee cake
directions: Mix sugars and shortening together.
Blend well with shortening as for pie crust.
Take out one cup of this for topping.
To the rest, add well beaten eggs, soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add nuts to the cup of mix and sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marble pound cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix at low speed until blended and then at high speed for 20 minutes. Reserve 1 cup batter in small bowl.
Pour other into greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan or 10 cup tube pan.
Mix chocolate syrup with cup of batter.
Spoon on top of cake batter and swirl with knife all through.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Tear the cake into bite size pieces.
Mix pudding, milk and sour cream together.
Pour over cake.
Pour thawed strawberries next and top with Cool Whip.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to the directions on package until almost done.
Spoon into bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place on top of vegetables.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup warm water; do not follow directions on box.
Mix all ingredients except for eggs.
Add eggs last, one at a time, beating well after each.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes (in preheated oven) at 350°.

title: mexi-chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving. Better if made the day before.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken, soup, celery, onion, almonds, salt, pepper, lemon juice and mayonnaise in large bowl and mix well.
Spoon a layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole or a 3-quart casserole.
Add layer of sliced eggs.
Repeat layers.
Cover with crushed potato chips and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Do not add potato chips until ready to bake.
Can be made day ahead.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple bars
directions: Beat together thoroughly eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix together and add to egg mixture flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts to mixture and pour in a pan, 10 x 13 x 2-inch. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix liquids in a large (4-cup) measuring cup or bowl.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in a greased iron skillet for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion in butter.
When limp, add 5 tablespoons flour. Stir well and add the milk.
When this will coat a spoon, add other ingredients, except cheese and chicken; mix well.
Add cheese and chicken (add cheese first as it will melt better).
Add this to spaghetti and top with reserved cheese.
Cook at 350° until it bubbles.

title: steve's famous chili
directions: Place ground chuck in skillet.
Combine chopped onion, chopped garlic, salt and chili powder.
Cook on medium high, stirring occasionally until meat is browned.;
Drain off grease.
Combine browned seasoned meat with the remainder of ingredients in a large soup kettle.
Cook on low to medium low heat.
After chili starts to bubble, allow it to simmer for at least 30 minutes before serving.
This will taste even better on the second day.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Slice chicken and cut into pieces.
Place in skillet with garlic and salt.
Saute in oil until tender.
Add drained mushrooms and green beans.
Stir to mix.
Add can of chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let set for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 6.
Quick and easy.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken "and" dumpling
directions: Cut up hen.
Place in large pot.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. Bring to a boil.
Decrease heat.
Cook slowly until meat is tender. Debone chicken.
Set aside.
Reserve broth.
Stir or sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening; add milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut dough in 1-inch squares.
Sprinkle with flour.
Bring broth to a brisk boil.
Drop 1-inch dough squares slowly into broth.
Cover tightly (no peeking).
Decrease heat to slow simmer 40 minutes. Add chicken and serve.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Hollow out Sheppard's bread and put artichoke mixture in the hollowed out bread.
Place on aluminum foil covered cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: christmas salad
directions: Heat 1 cup of boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple and continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Add cherry jello to pineapple and water.
Stir until dissolved; set aside and let cool to syrup stage.
Add cottage cheese and nuts.
Whip whipping cream; stir into mixture.
Let stand until chilled.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; divide dough in half.
Add food coloring to 1/2 of mixture.
Break into small pieces; roll out to form candy canes.
Twist the two colors together to form canes.
Brush with beaten egg white; sprinkle with crushed peppermint stick. Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 9 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables(no fat)
directions: In medium saucepan, combine onion, celery, carrots, garlic, the 1 cup of water, bouillon granules, tarragon and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes until veggies are crisp-tender.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water, then add oil and sugar.
Beat eggs in one at a time; add salt.
Add flour one cup at a time.
Let rise until dough doubles in size, then knead.
Make into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a spoon. Grease and flour bunt pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add sugar, flour and melted oleo gradually to beaten eggs.
Add buttermilk.
To this mixture, add flaked coconut and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: coffee with rum
directions: Put the spices, sugar and orange peel in a small pan and pour over the rum.
There should be enough to cover them.
Heat gently, shaking pan until the sugar has melted.
Pour in the hot coffee. Strain and serve.

title: alligator creole
directions: In
butter,
saute
alligator
about
minutes.
Add celery, onion and bell
pepper;
saute until tender.
Stir, do not burn.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until alligator is tender and liquids are of
the consistency of a nice sauce for pasta. Serve over rice and enjoy.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Just before serving, add canned chicken or tuna and shoestring potatoes.
Serve on lettuce.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches into an 8 x 8-inch pan and put about 1/2 cup of sugar on them.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large baking dish, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Use a 5-quart glass covered dish.
Melt butter in dish and stir in all ingredients, adding rice last.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Do not lift lid.
Let cool 15 minutes before you lift lid.
Then stir.

title: batter for fried onion rings
directions: Combine ingredients for batter.
Dip rings of raw onion into batter and fry in deep fryer.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to a boil for 3 minutes the vinegar, sugar, pepper and oil.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Drain corn, green beans and peas.
Mix all vegetables together.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seed in butter.
Mix cole slaw and onions in large bowl.
Add cooled almonds and sesame seed.
Mix dressing at time of serving.
Break Top Ramen over all and mix. May add red cabbage and more rice wine vinegar.

title: milky way cookies
directions: In large bowl beat oleo, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and baking powder; add and mix well.
Shape tablespoon of dough around candy forming a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: paw paw's refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, water and peppercorns.
Bring to a boil, then cool.
Add dill, hot pepper and garlic to a large container (1 gallon or more).
Pack cucumbers into container and add vinegar mixture (cooled) to cover cucumbers.
Let set at room temperature for 1 to 2 weeks, then refrigerate.
Keeps 3 to 4 months.

title: sweet and sour chicken or pork
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch cubes.
Combine cornstarch and soy sauce in dish and add meat; stir until coated.
Brown meat in oil 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine water with package of sauce blend.
Pour over meat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add carrot, pepper and pineapple. Cover and simmer 10 to 13 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: honey-mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Serve over baked ham, hot dogs and steamed vegetables.

title: sole bonne femme(sole with shallots in cream)
directions: In a wide frying pan, spread shallots, 1 tablespoon minced parsley and mushrooms.
Lay fish over vegetables, overlapping edges as little as possible.
Pour in wine.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with bread cubes. Cook, drain and cool sausage.
Beat eggs and milk; add ground mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir sausage into egg mixture.
Pour over bread cubes.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If glass dish, put in cold oven and heat together.

title: grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes.
Set skins aside.
Bring pulp to boiling point.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Press through sieve to remove seeds.
Add skins.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Let stand overnight. Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cranberries and rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening to size of coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Stir with fork until dough clings together.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: potato-celery soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, bouillon cubes, salt, and pepper in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until tender. Add milk and butter.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries well.
Mix sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla. Knead until smooth.
Pinch a small piece off and wrap around each cherry.
Place on well buttered pan and chill several hours. Melt paraffin and chips over hot water.
Dip each fondant ball into mix and place on buttered dish.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with sauce.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate or quiche pan.
Mix shrimp, crab, cheese, onion and pimentos.
Put into pan.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds by hand or 1 minute in a blender. Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Blend well.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Use cookie press on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, sugar, Crisco and salt.
Cool to lukewarm (about 10 minutes).
Soften yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in 1/4 cup of lukewarm water.
Stir yeast into the other lukewarm mixture.
Add 2 beaten eggs (room temperature).
Stir in 4 cups of flour.
Add 3 to 4 or more cups of flour to make a soft dough.
Do not knead.
Cover and put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon apple rolls
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk and 1/2 cup oil; stir just enough to hold dough together. Place on lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 strokes. Roll to 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Cover dough with combined apples, 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 1-inch thick pieces.
Combine 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup oil and nuts in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Place rolls in pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, until desired brownness.
Immediately turn upside-down onto large platter or cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes about 8 rolls.

title: chicken and chipped beef
directions: Arrange beef in bottom of 8 x 12 baking dish or pan. Wrap a strip of bacon around each chicken breast. Place chicken on top of beef. Spread undiluted soup over chicken. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours. Increase heat to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer, basting several times.

title: cucumber delight(from the kitchen of betty lyles)
directions: Slice cucumbers to fill jar.
Fill jar with cold vinegar mixture.
Seal and refrigerate 3 days before serving.
Delicious! Vinegar may be used for more cucumbers.

title: chili chicken
directions: Mix chicken and tomato sauce in Dutch oven.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat.
Prepare dumplings; drop by small teaspoonfuls onto hot chili.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle cheese on top of dumplings and serve.

title: sfinges (doughnuts)
directions: Sift together flour,
sugar
and
baking
powder.
Make well in center and add eggs
and
vanilla and slowly add milk, incorporating flour mixture.
Should
be a little thicker than pancake dough.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot, deep fat and fry until a golden brown.
Drain
on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle
with
honey.
Eat while piping hot! Great on Sunday morning!

title: pie crust
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients until grainy.
Add at least 8 tablespoons ice water.
Spoon together until it balls away from bowl.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time is 5 minutes.

title: meatless chili
directions: In a 5-quart saucepot, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cook, stirring 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add zucchini and carrots.
Cook, stirring 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add 2 pounds powdered sugar, sifted.

title: my only recipe
directions: Place first 2 items in car.
Place key in ignition and turn one time.
Drive car onto road.
Heat for nearest restaurant.

title: peach pie cake
directions: Pour the peaches (juice and all) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift the cake mix over the peaches.
Cut and drop the margarine over cake mix.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Mix brown sugar, pecans and 1/4 cup margarine.
Spread over cake and bake 10 more minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix 1/2 package of taco seasoning mix and cream cheese.
Spread onto a round platter.
Add in layers salsa, lettuce, tomato, pepper, cheese and onion.
Garnish outside with your favorite chips.

title: fisherman's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in skillet.
Add next 7 ingredients. Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Separate salmon into chunks, removing bones.
Combine macaroni, salmon, sauce and half the peas in large bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook remaining peas, using package directions.
Garnish with cooked peas.
Yields 6 servings.

title: four egg cake
directions: This is especially good with Cocoa Buttercream Frosting.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion in butter until meat is brown.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: picnic lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and water; boil 5 minutes.
Cool, then add lemon juice.
Put in jar and chill in refrigerator until ready for picnic.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts basic mixture at the picnic.
Add 3 quarts of water and ice and serve.
Yields 25 servings.

title: bob's soon-to-be-famous nonfat spaghetti sauce
directions: Stir together in 6-quart covered heavy aluminum pan.
Place in 250° oven for 6 hours stirring once after 1 hour.
Leave in pan for another 3 hours.
You could assemble the ingredients 1 hour before bedtime and set the oven to turn off six hours later.
Don't forget to stir after 1 hour, then leave it.

title: bible pudding
directions: Beat together 1 Corinthians, Isaiah, Psalms and Genesis.
Stir in John.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle 2 Chronicles on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: chili with chicken(low in fat)
directions: Spray nonstick Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Heat to medium-high.
Add chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until meat is browned.
Add tomatoes, beans, water, tomato paste, chili powder, cumin, salt, sugar and red pepper. Stir well.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings each with 197 calories, 7 grams fat and 39 milligrams cholesterol.

title: mom's rum sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring just to boiling over medium heat.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rum, vanilla and nutmeg. Great over apple pie.

title: sausage bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot.

title: indian spiced beans
directions: Wash beans.
Place all ingredients in 4-quart pan.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and cook 4 hours on low heat.

title: hedy's easy pie crust
directions: Mix together salt and flour; fork in Crisco.
Add 1/4 cup ice water.
Mix dough into a ball.

title: hot fruit drink
directions: Mix apple juice per directions on can.
Pour apple juice and pineapple juice in coffeepot.
Pour red hots in basket of coffeepot and perk.

title: salad
directions: Mix together.
Use dressing, if desired.
Wonderful as a light dinner or a side salad.

title: golden wedding anniversary punch
directions: Chill juices before mixing.
Mix all juices together, except ginger ale.
Do not add water to frozen juices.
Pour in a punch bowl; add ginger ale.

title: ham loaf
directions: Baste several times during baking until done.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Put Chex or Krispies in cake pan; crush slightly.
Combine in saucepan, sugar and Karo.
Heat to a full rolling boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal; mix evenly.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over cereal mixture.
Let cool.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: fresh tomato pizza
directions: You may use any other cheeses you prefer.

title: jicama orange salad
directions: In a medium nonmetal bowl, combine all ingredients except avocado; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add avocado; toss gently.
Drain salad, reserving orange juice dressing.
If desired, serve on lettuce-lined plates with reserved dressing.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: eight dollar fruit salad
directions: Drain all juices from fruit cocktail, oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: baked pastry shell
directions: Prepare Pastry For Single-Crust Pie as directed, except prick the bottom and sides with the tines of a fork.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat each 5 minutes.
Pour into shell.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: fried rice
directions: Season shrimp in the baking soda, oil and soy sauce.
Heat 6 tablespoons oil in wok; add shrimp.
Cook 1 minute.
Add eggs. Cook 1/2 minute.
Add cooked rice.
Cook enough rice for 6. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add green onions.
Keep stirring every time you add another ingredient.
Have rice cooked before you start the wok.

title: golden oyster stew
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese, pimento and seasonings. Continue to cook and stir often until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Add oysters and liquid.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until edge of oysters curl.
Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: wonder dessert cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Fold in fruit cocktail, juice and all.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and walnuts over top of batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter and eggs; mix well.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir into potatoes mixture.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add to mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until set.
Yield: one 9-inch pie.

title: cool strawberry cake
directions: Bake sheet cake as directed.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups of hot water only.
While cake is still warm, use a fork to punch holes in cake and spoon Jell-O mixture directly into holes, allowing mixture to penetrate cake.
Let set 30 minutes before refrigerating.
When cold, spread crushed strawberries over cake. Cover with whipped cream.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown in margarine or oil.
In same skillet, pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Top with Mozzarella, then Parmesan cheese.
Do not stir.
Cover, cooking, on very low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
(May sit at this point.)

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Drain.
Add cream cheese that has been melted.
Add all other ingredients except biscuits.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until casserole begins to bubble around edges.
Place biscuits around edge.
Place half of stuffed olive in center of each biscuit.
Bake 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: wrapped fish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put each fish fillet on a piece of aluminum foil large enough to enclose it.
Brush with margarine; top with onion and tomato.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and oregano. Season with pepper.
Fold the foil over the top of the fillet and crimp the edges together securely.
Put the fillets in a baking dish just large enough to hold them.
Pour in 1/4 inch of water and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve the fish in its wrapping.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form a ball.
Chill until firm and roll in 2/3 cup pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease (9 x 1 1/4-inch) pie plate. Prepare mashed potatoes as directed on package for 4 servings except decrease water to 1 cup and omit milk.
Stir in egg, green onions and sour cream.
Press potato mixture against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Prick bottom and side with fork.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: mexican manicotti(this is one of pastor kevin's favorite dishes.)
directions: Combine uncooked meat, refried beans, oregano and cumin.
Mix well.
Fill uncooked shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Combine water and picante sauce and pour over shells.
Cover your dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes until noodles are tender.
About midpoint of your baking time, very carefully turn the noodles over.
Combine sour cream, green onions and olives.
Spread over noodles.
Take note which direction you placed your noodles before adding sour cream mixture so you will know how to take them out.
Finally, add cheese for the final layer.
Place back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cook apples and chop.
Season to taste with sugar and brown sugar.
Roll each biscuit out flat and cut in 3 wedges. Put apples in wedge and wrap.
Place wrapped wedges in large casserole. Boil for 3 minutes 1 stick margarine, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup water and cinnamon to taste.
Pour mixture over wrapped apples.
If you have apples left over, just put around edges.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: easy nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cream cheese.
Spread over 9-inch pie plate on bottom.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over chili.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: frozen peach cream pie
directions: In a blender, blend chopped peaches until smooth, set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in Eagle Brand, then peaches, lemon juice and extract.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour equal portions into crusts.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with fresh peach slices, if desired.

title: california roll appetizer
directions: Have ready the tortillas.
Mix together the next five ingredients.
Add chicken, if desired.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll tortillas and set in casserole dish with tortillas seam side down.
Cover with a damp towel.
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice.
Serve with salsa as an appetizer.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of an 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: whole wheat sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except last 2; blend well.
Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla with fork or spoon. Sift together flour, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Add sugar.
Mix with the liquid.
Add nuts.
Cook in tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until slushy.

title: beef and corn kabobs
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and spices in glass container.
Add beef; stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 4 or more hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove beef.
Place beef, corn, peppers and tomatoes about 1/4-inch apart.
Brush with marinade.
Cover and grill 4 to 5 inches form coals.
Turn and marinate occasionally for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: sugar cookies or tea cakes
directions: Combine Crisco, salt, lemon rind and nutmeg. Add sugar and cream well. Add beaten eggs and milk, mixing well. Sift flour with baking powder and soda. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Flatten cookies by stamping with bottom of flat glass dipped in water. Sprinkle cookies with sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: strogie
directions: Cut porterhouse into small strips (bite sized).
Heat oil and black pepper in skillet (hot).
Toss steak pieces in flour.
Remove and shake off excess flour.
Brown in hot oil.
Reserve steak. Cool skillet slightly (add more oil or liquid, Worcestershire). Add slowly and cook chopped onion.
When onion is transparent, return steak to skillet, add a big dollop of sour cream over all and warm slightly.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add all other ingredients.
Mix well, then put in a bowl.
Add a sprig of parsley for a garnish, if you like.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or a large cast-iron skillet and make sure that the entire bottom of the pan is covered.
Then place the pan in the freezer.
After the butter or margarine is frozen, drain the juice from the 2 cans of pineapple in a large measuring cup.
While the pineapple is draining, remove the pan from the freezer and spread the brown sugar evenly in the bottom of the pan before the butter or margarine melts.
Then decorate the brown sugar with the sliced pineapple and fill all of the remaining space with the pineapple chunks.
Place whole maraschino cherries in the center of each pineapple slice.

title: spicy breast of chicken
directions: Season chicken breasts lightly with seasoning salt and pepper. Place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix lime juice, salad dressing mix, and butter.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove cover for the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with the salt, water and ice cubes and let stand for 3 hours.
Make a syrup of the remaining ingredients. Boil syrup mixture for 5 minutes. Drain cucumbers. Drop in boiling syrup but do not boil after adding cucumbers.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: mama lous cake
directions: Grease a large pan, larger than 13 x 9-inch.

title: salmon spread
directions: Microwave oleo & bouillon just to melt.
Mix all ingredients together & beat with mixer until smooth.
Serve on crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop dough into small balls on cookie sheet.
Flatten down with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gurkensalat(cucumber salad)
directions: Peel cucumbers and into very thin slices.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over cucumbers.
Marinate about 20 minutes.
Drain off liquid, toss cucumbers with sour cream. top with fresh parsley and serve.
Serves 4-5.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Brown meat; pour in colander and rinse under hot water to remove any fat.
Mix spaghetti sauce with meat.
Spray casserole dish with nonfat spray.
Layer noodles, cheese, meat and sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, meat and sauce, noodles, rest of meat and sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Note:
You must taste this recipe as you go.
Measurements are according to taste.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine sugar and mustard seed; let come to a boil.
Set aside and cool.
Then add remaining ingredients; mix these together and let set for several hours or overnight.
This will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: green rice
directions: Chop all greens in processor. Bake rice and when done add cheese, milk, and everything else. Bake in covered casserole bowl for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into a buttered 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour and oleo; sprinkle over the sliced apples.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: mama's sweet potato puffs
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes until tender; drain.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla flavoring.
Mash potatoes.
Set aside until the potatoes are cold.
When cold, mold potatoes around individual marshmallows, covering completely.
Roll each puff in crushed corn flakes.
Place each puff in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish about 1 inch apart.
Heat in oven for about 5 minutes or until marshmallows are hot.

title: angel rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, scald 1/2 cup milk with 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add salt and oil to mixture.
In cup, dissolve sugar in warm water and add yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
When milk is cooled, add yeast mixture.
Mix in flour to make soft dough.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Turn on floured board and knead 5 minutes.
Make into rolls.
Let rise until dough doubles.
Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Mix eggs, water, baking powder and flour until able to roll. Roll to desired thickness and cut.

title: norwegian noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until just barely tender.
Strain the noodles and rinse with cold water; place in bowl.
Melt the butter and put half in a large casserole or baking dish, coating the sides and bottom.
Preheat oven to 350° and place the empty dish in the oven.
Add cinnamon, raisins, sugar, salt and almond extract to the noodles.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs; add milk and beat again until well blended.
Add to the noodles with the remainder of the melted butter.
Stir well.
Pour into the heated casserole dish and bake until the top is golden brown, 1 hour or longer.
Serves 8.

title: honey granola bread
directions: Mix water and yeast; add 3 cups flour and salt.
In saucepan, heat milk, honey and butter until warm.
Add to flour mixture. Add eggs and beat.
Stir in granola and rest of flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down, divide into 3.
Place in loaf pans; let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening together, add buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 c warm water.
Add to dry ingredients. Work dough and knead.
Roll out for biscuits.
Let rise on baking sheet 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake at 450 degrees until golden brown on top.

title: peanut butter reese's squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, a little at a time, and mix well. Add vanilla.
Mix well, then press down in a 9-inch pan.
Melt candy bar and pour on top in very thin layer.
Let harden before cutting.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to a soft ball stage (on candy thermometer) on low heat.
Pour in nuts.
Stir until stiff and loses gloss.
Pour onto wet towel to form roll.
Cool in towel, then wrap in foil.
This makes a roll about 18 inches long.
Slice as ready to serve.

title: golden apple pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in small bowl. Cut in oleo until fine.
Put over sliced apples in pie shell.
(I put about 1/4 cup water of the apple, flour and sugar mixture.) Put the top crust on, brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onion in gallon jar.
Pour cold liquid over and keep in refrigerator.
Ready in 5 days.
Keeps 9 months.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish. Trim crusts off bread and cut bread slices into cubes; place in dish. Add cheese and sausage. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top. Chill one hour or overnight. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate biscuits into 20 pieces. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuits into melted butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits in a single layer, overlapping slightly in a deep dish pan.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Place an apple slice between each biscuit and around outer edge of pan.
Mix nuts with remaining sugar mixture and sprinkle over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together; chill.

title: walnut spice kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, mixed with spices.
Fold in chopped walnuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion.
Cook according to directions. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water in an iron skillet until it spins a thread.
Beat egg whites and slowly pour in syrup, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour onto greased foil.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread bottom with apple slices and sprinkle 1/3 cup water over top.
Mix dry ingredients, then add the small butter pieces, one at a time, until it looks like coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle this over the apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 300 degrees.
Check it because sometimes it takes a little longer.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: *Three large breasts boiled long enough to pull off the bones or leftover fried chicken pulled off the bones is great.

title: pound cake(alabama tech extension service)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and continue beating.
Then add egg yolks (beaten until thick and lemon colored), egg whites (beaten until stiff), flour, mace and flavoring.
Beat vigorously 5 minutes.
Bake in deep pan in very moderate oven (300° to 325°) for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chili beef and corn casserole
directions: In small bowl, blend 1 cup beef broth, tomato paste and taco seasoning mix; set aside.
In a saucepan over high heat, combine remaining broth and enough water to equal 1 3/4 cups liquid; heat to boil.
Add rice and cook according to package directions.

title: tout de suite pralines
directions: In a 4 or 5-quart glass or ceramic dish, stir together buttermilk, sugar, pecans, salt and butter. Cook in microwave oven on High for 12 minutes, stirring at 4-minute intervals. Stir in baking soda until foamy. Cook on High 1 minute. (This last step gives the pralines a caramel color). Add vanilla and beat mixture until tacky, about 1 minute. Drop by teaspoon on a sheet of foil or waxed paper.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients and cook for one hour.

title: broccoli noodle cheese soup
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles.
Cook until noodles are soft (10 minutes). Add broccoli and cook for 5 minutes more.
Add milk.
After milk mixture is heated through, add cheese.
Stir gently until cheese is melted.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve liquid). Core apples, cut in half and scoop out seeds with melon baller. Cube apples (1/2-inch cubes). Beat egg. In small saucepan, combine pineapple juice, egg, sugar, flour and vinegar using a wire whisk. Over medium heat, stir with a wooden spoon until thickened. Pour mixture into large mixing bowl. Cool. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate. When thoroughly cool, fold Cool Whip into cooked mixture and add 1/2 cup peanuts.

title: queens pudding
directions: In a double boiler bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour or until a knife comes out clear.
Layer brown sugar in top of double boiler. Place bread cubes next.
Mix remaining ingredients (except nutmeg). Pour over cubes.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: collectors cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla (beat 1 minute).
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Mix well with beater. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 2 (8-inch) round cake pans or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Layer dip into a sheet cake pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: *You may want to reduce some of these ingredients to suit your own taste.

title: six week muffins(makes 60 muffins)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sopaipillas(fried puffs)
directions: Place water in bowl, sprinkle in dry yeast and let stand until dissolves.
In a pan combine milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and stir in butter.
Let cool to lukewarm; then stir in yeast mixture.
While stirring, add beaten egg. Gradually beat in 3 cups of flour, working in last 1/2 cup by hand.
Dough will be soft not sticky.

title: ramaki
directions: Wrap bacon slices around water chestnuts (cut bacon slice in half first); secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking pan.
Pour barbecue sauce over wrapped water chestnuts.
Bake at 450° until bacon is done.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and ground nuts. Work together like pie dough until crumbly.
Press into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: polynesian pork and shrimp appetizers
directions: In skillet, brown pork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Makes 12 to 16 servings for appetizers.

title: fettucini with ham and peas
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Stir in ham and peas.
Over medium heat, heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and keep warm. Cook fettucini, omitting salt.
Drain well.
Place in large serving bowl.
Add 1/2 cup softened butter; stir until completely melted. Add Parmesan cheese and sour cream, stirring to coat.
Fold ham mixture into fettucini.
Add pepper.
Serve with hot bread, green salad and red wine.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and water. Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Stir well. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Bake in 11 x 17-inch sheet pan in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer in airtight container.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese in shaker.
Ice (like cake) on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: glazed roasted turkey
directions: Wash turkey and pat dry.
Rub inside with olive oil.
Spoon stuffing inside.
Rub turkey with butter on the outside.
Cover loosely with foil.
Roast at 325° for 4 hours.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 350° oven.
Add graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut, nuts and sweetened condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber apple rings
directions: First Day:
Soak cucumbers 24 hours in lime and 1 gallon water.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all
together
and	bake
at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Place sausage in pot with cold water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pierce sausage to drain fat, then cut into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces. Place in casserole.
Cover with a combination of chili sauce, catsup, boiling water, bay leaf and allspice. Top with sliced onion. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 40 minutes.
Add wine.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf and allspice. Serve with rye bread.

title: waffle batter
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff.
Beat yolks until golden.
Add milk and beat 1 minute longer.
Add dry ingredients; beat until blended.
Add melted butter and beat in thoroughly. Fold in egg whites.
Make waffles in your favorite iron.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll steak in 1/4 cup flour and salt. Brown onions, garlic and mushrooms in oil for 5 minutes. Add steak and brown evenly. Remove meat, onions and mushrooms from pan. Add flour to drippings. Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until thick. Add sour cream and heat to simmer. Add beef and vegetables. Serve on hot cooked rice, toast or noodles, cooked or chow mein.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine butter, milk and caramels.
Heat until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pur over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Top with remaining batter and bake 20 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage until done, breaking into small pieces.
Drain. Brown pepper, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients in a large baking dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese). Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: jalapeo cornbread
directions: Prepare the recipe for cornbread. When the batter is ready, add the minced jalapeo chile and mix in well. Pour the batter into a greased baking pan and bake as the recipe directs. Serve hot.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add ingredients in order.
Place in a 2-quart mold or long, flat dish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Using spoon, beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired. Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool and cut in squares.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas soft in a little oil.
Fill with grated cheese, chicken and onion.
Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 1/2 hour).

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon yellow. Add sugar gradually.
Beat whiskey in gradually.
Stir in cream and milk.
Beat egg whites; stir into mixture. Add vanilla. Nutmeg to taste (optional).
Let stand overnight.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese, chop pimentos and mix with other ingredients. Chill 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
