title: pasta carbonara
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Saute onion, garlic and bacon together.
Drain pasta and return to pot.
Over low heat, stir in eggs and Parmesan.
Heat until eggs are set.
Add bacon, onion and garlic mixture with bacon grease.
Stir and serve with Parmesan for sprinkling on top.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine ingredients and boil until mixture forms a good, firm ball in cold water.
Add about 2 tablespoons of butter when removed from heat.
Let cool, then beat until its too firm to spread on cake.
Add a little milk or cream to mixture and icing will remain smooth.
This icing never gets hard.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out thin and cut.
Great in homemade chicken noodle soup.

title: strawberry cream cheese delights
directions: Wash strawberries; gently pat dry.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, lemon juice and lemon peel; blend well.
Dip berries into cream cheese mixture, coating bottom half of berry.
Roll berry in chopped pistachios.
Arrange on serving plate.
Cover; refrigerate until serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets and tender stalks into bite size pieces. Discard woody stems.
Place first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss gently. Chill 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook breasts and remove bones.
Put chicken in casserole dish. Blend sour cream and soup.
Pour this mixture over chicken. Crush crackers.
Add poppy seed to crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Drizzle oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: pancakes
directions: My mon makes it with some powder and she makes milk with it. She has to stir it and she has to make it like a dough.
She puts it in a big bowl and it's a pan. She has to flatten it out and then it looks like a pancake.
She cooks it. Then I come eat it.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-size bowl.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter squares
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Add flour and chips to peanut butter mixture.
Stir well.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: These are great for kid's parties. Make these instead of the traditional cake and your party will be a hit!

title: banana cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown; let cool.

title: hamburger chicken fried steak
directions: Mix ground beef with salt and pepper to taste.
Shape into 6 not too thin patties.
Dip in flour, then in buttermilk, then in flour.
Fry slowly in deep fat until brown.

title: "no cook" fudge (peanut butter)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add vanilla and oleo or margarine. Beat with electric mixer, then add peanut butter.
It is very stiff.
Spread in large pan and refrigerate for a few hours or more.

title: italian party platter
directions: Lay 1 tube crescent rolls flat in the bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Layer salami, ham, Provolone and peppers on top of rolls. Repeat the salami, ham, Provolone and pepper layer the second time.
Mix the eggs and grated cheese together; spoon over the top.
Lay the second tube crescent rolls over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then 30 minutes uncovered.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Add drained sauerkraut and rest of ingredients.
Marinate overnight.

title: candy apples
directions: Combine caramel and 2 tablespoons water in double boiler. Cook until smooth.
Dip apples in caramel until covered.
Roll bottom half of apple in nuts.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in ungreased casserole.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add flour to hamburger; cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic and cinnamon.
Pour over corn.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine eggs and cottage cheese.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Coat chicken with flour.
Cook chicken in shortening over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic to skillet. Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add chicken to sauce.
Cover tightly and simmer 40 minutes, or until thickest pieces are fork-tender.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: apple treats
directions: Mix cream cheese and raisins.
Core apple and stuff with cream cheese mixture.
Slice apple or eat whole.

title: pop-pop's chicken corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion until tender (5 minutes).
Blend in flour and bouillon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk; heat to boiling, then simmer (avoid a hard boil), stirring until mixture thickens.
Add potatoes, corn, chicken, green and red peppers and bay leaf.
Stir in hard-boiled eggs.
Makes approximately 6 servings.
Very rich; serve with green salad.

title: teriyaki burgers
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice. Combine soy sauce, catsup and 1 tablespoon pineapple juice.
Remove 3 tablespoons mixture and set aside.
To remainder, add marjoram, garlic powder and ginger. Blend well.
Add onion, ground beef and Chex.
Mix and shape into 4 patties. Add 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar to reserved soy sauce mixture. Grill or broil burgers, brushing with mixture.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix gelatine, 3/4 cup sugar and salt thoroughly in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Add to gelatine. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon rind, juice and vanilla.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
While mixture is chilling, prepare Crumb Topping.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift flour once, then sift again together with sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine grated carrots, undrained pineapple, beaten eggs, vanilla and oil. Blend well.
Add the dry ingredients and stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 lightly greased 9-inch layer cake pans lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool and frost between layers and on top and sides with Whipped Cream Frosting.

title: danish style cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice paper thin.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze cucumbers in your hand so all juice goes away and place dry cucumbers in a glass jar.
Mix vinegar with water, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Very delicious with meat.

title: hot chicken salad iii
directions: Mix all together, except the cheese, in a 9 x 13-inch pan or slightly larger lasagna pan.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes approximately 15 to 20 serving.
Serve with croissants and a salad. Very filling.

title: dressing for chow chow or pepper cabbage
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt.

title: fruit punch
directions: In a gallon container, mix pineapple juice and frozen lemonade.
Shake well.
Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour this in gallon container with juice and lemonade mixture.
Freeze.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Shake before using.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: Blend Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Add deviled ham and olives.
Shape into a log.
Roll in pecans and chill.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix together all except Jell-O.
When mixed, add dry Jell-O. Stir well.

title: cheesy egg nest
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a hole in center of bread with 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Butter one side of bread.
Place buttered side down on lightly greased baking sheet.
Butter other side of bread. Crack egg into cup; carefully pour egg into center of bread. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and grated cheese.
Bake for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: This tastes like pumpkin pie without the work of doing the crust.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Boil cabbage for 5 minutes in enough water to cover; drain well.
Combine 2 tablespoons melted margarine, flour and salt and pepper in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until smooth and thickened. Alternate layers of cabbage, cheese and white sauce in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes on 350° until brown.

title: apple good
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly dust with flour in 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and chopped nuts. Coat apples with this mixture and place in baking dish.
Mix the rest of ingredients and pat on apple mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: This recipe is great for an all church covered dish dinner!

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook milk, juice of 1 lemon and egg yolks over low heat.
Pour over all fruit which has been drained.
Stir in whipping cream last.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: hershey cocoa buttercream frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in deep bowl and beat until fluffy.

title: no-fuss no-muss beef
directions: Cut up onions and saute them in a deep pot.
Add the steak and jar of horseradish sauce.
When the jar is empty, fill it with the cooking wine, then pour the wine into the pot with the previous ingredients.
Cover the pot and cook on the top of the stove over medium heat until the meat is tender.
In a separate pot, cook the noodles.
When meat is done, cut it into slices or chunks and serve over the noodles (there should be lots of gravy to use).

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and cream cheese in boiling water.
Add 7-Up; mix well.
Chill until thick.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Return to refrigerator; let set until firm.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine Milnot and sugar in heavy saucepan (4 quart).
Add marshmallows and butter.
Cook over low heat until melted.
(Heat may be turned to medium.)
Bring mixture to a full boil and stir 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted. Blend vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly buttered pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Allow to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix.
Form ball and refrigerate.
Roll in nuts after 2 hours.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Put dates, nuts, soda and butter in bowl.
Add boiling water and let stand.
Beat egg.
Add all ingredients to date mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cheese potato wedges
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into wedges.
Dip in melted butter. Arrange in single layer on pan or on cookie sheet.

title: green chili burritos
directions: Pull meat apart with fingers, chip roast into small pieces. Do not cut with knife.
Mix ingredients and simmer for 1 hour. Serve on large tortilla shell with lettuce, tomatoes, onions, grated cheese, sour cream and salsa sauce.

title: brunch quesadillas with fruit salsa
directions: Fruit Salsa: Combine strawberries, pear, cilantro and honey in medium bowl; set aside. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons cheese on one half of each tortilla. Top with 1/3 cup Fruit Salsa (drain and discard any liquid from fruit) and another 2 tablespoons cheese. Fold tortilla in half. Brush top of each folded tortilla with melted margarine; turn and brown other side. Remove to serving plate. Cut each tortilla in half. Serve with remaining salsa. Garnish with sour cream.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put a layer of potatoes in a greased baking dish and sprinkle with some of the flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat until all potatoes are used.
Pour milk over potatoes and dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
If not brown enough, place under broiler.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine in top of double boiler, beating with rotary beater until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Continue beating until thick enough to spread.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix with above alternately with water.
Pour into two floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add flour to creamed ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add coconut, pineapple, carrots and nuts and mix in well.

title: cranberry refrigerator cake
directions: Mix cranberries, banana and sugar.
Add vanilla to Eagle Brand. Place 1/2 of wafers in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread milk mixture over wafers.
Top with cranberry mixture.
Top with whipped cream and nuts.
Sprinkle on rest of wafers and chill for 4 hours before serving.

title: crab quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust per package directions. Beat eggs.
Stir in cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Pat crabmeat dry and sprinkle crabmeat and cheese into pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over crabmeat and cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes.
Let quiche stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese, butter, flour, wine and Tabasco thoroughly with a fork.
Put pastry together into large ball.
Take 1 teaspoon pastry at a time and wrap around one small sausage.
Roll in palms so links are completely covered with pastry, covering will be thin.
Be sure none of the sausage shows through.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake in 400° oven, about 15 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish and set in oven to melt.
Mix peaches with sugar and set aside.
Make a batter with remaining ingredients and pour over melted margarine; do not stir.
Gently spoon peaches on top of batter; do not stir into batter.
Bake until crust is light brown and puffy, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour and baking soda; add pudding, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into egg mixture and fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
You can add about 1/2 cup milk as mixture is very thick.
Spoon in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Prebake pie shell until light brown.
Saute onions and shallots in butter.
Add ham (only to warm).
Put mixture in pie shell.
Beat eggs and Pet milk.
Add cheese and put mixture in pie shell.
Stir all ingredients in shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and spread on packaged toast rounds. Use 1 heaping teaspoonful per round, carefully spreading to very edge.

title: easy chili cheese dip
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, combine chili and cream cheese. Heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Add picante sauce to taste.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender. Add ground beef.
Cook until meat loses pink color.
Add tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce, chili pepper and garlic. Mix well.
Simmer over low heat 3 to 4 hours.
Thin with tomato juice, if needed.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon until crisp and chop up.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, water, salt, pepper and flour.
Cook until tender.
Stir in clams, milk, cream and butter.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Make a stiff batter in large bowl.
Put batter in a larger greased bowl or divide into 2 bowls.
Cover tightly and let rise for 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar.

Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and beat into creamed mixture. Toss the blueberries with the 2 tablespoons flour and fold them and the nuts into the batter gently. Spoon onto ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter; add eggs, vanilla and pecans. Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture.
Place in 350° oven; lower heat to 325° and cook 50 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: single crust for custard pie
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour Wesson oil and milk together, do not
stir.
Add
all
at once to flour.
Stir until mixed. Press into smooth ball.
Cut in half; flatten slightly.
Place 1/2 between
sheets
of
waxed paper.
Dampen table top to prevent slipping.
Roll out gently to edges of paper, peel off top
paper, place
paper side up in 8 to 9-inch pie pan, peel off
paper. Ease
and
form
pastry into pan.
Trim even with rim.
Bake crust before filling with custard.
This pie crust is a no-failing crust as long as the exact amount is used.

title: tri-tip roast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in shallow pan.
Season to taste.
Cook for 25-30 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and cook for an additional 25 - 30 minutes. Remove from heat and let meat rest 5 - 10 minutes before carving. Roast will be medium to medium rare.
Slice across grain.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: black magic cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add chocolate, beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add nuts; fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pans and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil or microwave chicken breasts, cool, debone, dice and set aside.
Mix soup, Veg-All, milk, pepper and thyme to taste.
Add chicken.
Follow directions on pie crust box for 2 crust pie.
Add filling, top crust and flute edges.
Slit top layer of crust. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: swiss potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add half and half.
Pour over hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: yummy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bring soups to a boil and pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces in rice/soup mixture.
Cover pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Check chicken for doneness, cook 15 minutes more, if necessary.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain.
Fry bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Stir about every 20 minutes.

title: jane's "killer" macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni for seven minutes.
Drain.
Layer 1/2 of the macaroni in a sprayed casserole dish along with 1/2 of the Velveeta cubes and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese.
Repeat so that you have 2 layers of everything.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 400° for 1 hour; drain excess fat.
Top with 1 cup barbecue sauce and 3/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: cereal candy
directions: In large bowl, combine cereals and peanuts and set aside.
In a large pan, combine sugar, cream and syrup and bring to a boil and cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Pour over cereal mixture. Stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 48 pieces.

title: oklahoma stew
directions: Boil stew meat until brown.
In a large stew pot, add all ingredients and water.
Cook on medium-low heat for 2 hours or until meat falls apart and potatoes are soft.
Serve with cornbread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rump beef roast
directions: Place roast in foil; put in a roasting pan.
Put in oven at 350°.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven; add all other items.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Remove roast from pan.
Slice very thin and return to pan with potatoes or place on platter.
Place potatoes around roast.
Put liquid over sliced beef.

title: jessica's oatmeal pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and syrup; mix well.
Add oats, coconut and butter; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: walnut spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Beat all ingredients except walnuts on low speed, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Mix together and let set.

title: lasagna by mike hoover
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add meats and brown. When brown, add all other ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours over low heat, covered.
While the sauce is simmering grate the cheese in a large bowl and set in the refrigerator to chill.
Beat the eggs well and add to the cottage cheese; also put in the fridge to chill.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package instructions; drain and cool.
In a 12 x 18-inch pan, put enough sauce in the bottom of the pan which has been buttered to cover it.
Follow with a layer of noodles, layer of Mozzarella cheese and egg cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat layers until pan is full.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
The pan can be put in the refrigerator overnight if you are not going to serve it right away.
If you do it will take about 90 minutes of cooking to get hot to the middle.
Serves 18.

title: brown sugar date cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Make hole in cookie dough; put teaspoonful of dates in hole and put 1/2 teaspoonful cookie dough on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as directed on box.
Brown hamburger meat; drain off grease.
Add sauce and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
In oblong dish, put a thin layer of meat sauce, then a layer of drained lasagna, meat sauce, Cheddar cheese.
Continue until you end up with meat sauce on top.
Cover top of meat sauce with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients (except tomato paste) for 20 minutes; stir frequently.
Add tomato paste.
Cook another 10 minutes, uncovered. Put in blender a little at a time on puree.
Do not fill blender to full because the mixture will spill over when turned on.
Freeze or cold pack.
This is an excellent spaghetti sauce.

title: spears' german hot potato salad
directions: Cook whole potatoes in boiling salted water.
Cool, peel and cube potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Break into pieces over the potatoes.
Heat onion and celery in drippings until partly done, then add vinegar and sugar. Heat to boiling. Pour over potatoes and mix slightly.
Warm just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: fudge no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, oleo and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove; add oats, vanilla, peanut butter and nuts.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.
Cool and eat.

title: jambalaya
directions: Chop and saute onion and pepper in a little butter.
Boil water and bouillon cubes.
When cubes are dissolved, add everything else and cook until rice is done.

title: honey curried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Pat dry.
Remove skin if you wish.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll chicken pieces in butter mixture to coat both sides, then arrange meaty side up in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and richly glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Chop each vegetable separately in food processor.
Add salt, stir, and allow to sit overnight.
Drain.
In the morning, combine remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and add vegetables.
Bring to a boil again, reduce heat and simmer approximately 3 minutes. Put into hot jars and seal.

title: microwave bean dip
directions: Let the cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Spread cream cheese on the bottom of casserole dish; on top of cream cheese mixture, spread refried beans, then a layer of chili.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over entire surface.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.
Chill 1 hour.

title: meltaway cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in sugar, flour and salt.
Roll a ball of mixture about the size of a small pecan.
Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Cook about 8 minutes. When partially cooled, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: cheery cherry cheese tarts
directions: Place cupcake liners into the muffin pan.
Crush graham crackers into a bowl.
Melt butter and add to crackers.
Mix until moistened.
Place 1 tablespoon mixture into liners and press down with juice glass.
Set aside.
Cream together cream cheese and eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Mix until smooth.
Fill the liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
(Tarts may be frozen and thawed for later use.)
Place spoonful of cherry filling on top of tarts.
Yields 24 tarts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs until frothy, then beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until it is thick and lemon colored.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into loaf pan generously greased with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.	Bake, covered, until chicken is done (about 1 hour and 30 minutes).

title: smoked sausage over rice
directions: Dice sausage into bite size pieces.
Place in a large Teflon skillet. Cover with onions and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat with lid on until brown on each side.
Save drippings. Cook rice until firm.
Pour into large baking dish. Add margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce and water to drippings.
Pour over rice and mix.
Salt to taste.
Pour hot smoked sausage along with onions and pepper over rice.
Cover tightly and let stand or place in warm oven for 10 minutes.

title: fried cheese
directions: Heat oil in frying pan to a depth of 2 to 3-inches, dip cheese in egg then in bread crumbs.
Fry in heated oil until golden brown.
Carefully lift cubes from oil and drain.
Makes about 24.

title: baked jambalaya
directions: Put all ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Stir and bake at 350 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt
stick oleo in an 8 x 13-inch dish.
Mix graham crackers
and
spread
around dish bottom and sides for crust. Mix well
2 sticks oleo, powdered sugar and eggs; spread over crust. Next,
layer
bananas,
pineapple,
pecans and whipped cream,
in that order.
Drizzle over top with chocolate syrup and
decorate with cherries.
Cool in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours at least. Cut in squares to serve.
Can be prepared the day before. Delicious!!!

title: talarena
directions: Brown meat, onion and peppers.
Add garlic, corn, tomatoes, pimientos and seasonings.
Cook until slightly thick.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and cheese in 13 x 9-inch pan.
End with cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in peeling.
Cool.
Peel and cut in squares. Cook bacon.
Save 1/4 cup of drippings.
Set aside.
Add sugar, flour and vinegar to drippings.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Mix potato, bacon, green peppers and pimento. Pour dripping mix over potato mixture and mix.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well to blend.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in casserole dish.
Pour into pudding mixture, reserving just a small amount in dish.
Turn corn pudding into dish.
Bake in hot (375°) oven for 30 minutes.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in oil until crumbly but not hard.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve with toasted hamburger buns.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat, onions and celery; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: make your own fish sticks
directions: Wash fillets; pat dry with paper towel.
Have a grown up assistant cut them up into long pieces.
Preheat oven to 400°. Spread bread crumbs out on wax paper.
Break eggs into bowl and beat them.
Dip fish into eggs, then bread crumbs until coated. Lay into baking pan.
Pour melted margarine or butter over each fish stick.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brian's cheesy skillet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, onions, salt and water in heavy skillet. Cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add to potatoes the milk, melted butter and cheese.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Brown bread crumbs in 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Crumble fried bacon on top of crumbs.

title: braised duck
directions: Place ducks in baking pan, breasts up.
Season each duck with 1/2 teaspoon each: celery salt, curry powder, pepper and salt. Let stand for about 1 hour.
Add onion and celery to the pan along with 1/2-inch of water.
Bake at 500° for about 20 minutes.
Turn the ducks and bake until backs are brown.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 300°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Dry lettuce with toweling.
Tear lettuce into a large salad bowl.
For each eight cups loosely packed leaves, cook four strips of bacon until crisp in skillet.
Crumble.
Reserve.
To bacon fat in skillet add and stir in 1/2 cup diced green onions, 1 tablespoon sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/3 cup vinegar. Cook two minutes.
Pour hot dressing over lettuce.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Toss to coat greens evenly.
Makes four servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place beef, soups, mushrooms, salt and pepper in crock-pot and cook overnight (or until very tender), stirring occasionally. Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour meat mixture over; sprinkle with cheese and cook at 350° about 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix, cocoa, vanilla, margarine, milk, red food coloring and eggs. Add soda and vinegar. Make 2 or 3 layers. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cream of coconut. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Remove cake from the oven and punch holes all over the top with a big fork. Pour cream of coconut over the cake.
After cake cools, cover with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix and spread in 8 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over layer of crumbs, then spread prepared pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 12.

title: karo krazy crunch

into water.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; take off heat.
Pour over

after cooled in covered container. Barely salt.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in bowl.
Dip each biscuit in sugar mixture and layer in Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and add remaining sugar mixture and pour over top of rolls.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Melt cheese in a separate bowl. Once cheese is melted, immediately add to hamburger and sausage. Add relish.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (or two 8 x 8-inch pans) with Pam.
Put one or two tablespoons spaghetti sauce on bottom of pan.
Boil noodles according to directions. Combine softened cream cheese, sour cream and 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce.
Combine with drained egg noodles.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Pour mixture into pan.
Top with Mozzarella and about 1 to 1 1/2 cups of spaghetti sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with remaining spaghetti sauce.

title: banana carrot cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
In a large bowl, cream the butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
In a small bowl, mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Blend flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas, ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in carrots and raisins.
Turn into baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan; cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes 16 squares.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Stir together powdered milk, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in water. Turn on floured surface and knead to smooth ball.

title: "green" salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a bowl.
Set aside pineapple.
Mix pudding mix with pineapple juice until dissolved.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Slowly add Cool Whip until you reach desired consistency.

title: lemon pudding pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
a
dash
of
salt
and flour.	Stir in melted margarine, lemon peel and juice.
Combine milk and egg yolks. Add
to
lemon mixture.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into an 8 x
8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place some small rocks in the bottom of Dutch oven to elevate baking pan.
Pour water 2-inch deep in Dutch
oven.
Place
baking pan in oven.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: cake 'n cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake batter as directed.
Pour approximately 3 tablespoons of batter into ice cream cone.
Set on baking
pan or into muffin tins.
Allow cake to cool.
Then mound with frosting.
Round them to look like a scoop of ice cream. When these cakes are done, they will be the size of ice cream in a cone.
Top the frosting with decorations.
Makes 12 cones.
Kids love these.

title: irish coffee
directions: In a warmed wine glass, place sugar and fill with coffee. Mix.
Add whiskey and top with whipped cream.

title: favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Grate cheese.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook until it bubbles. Warm milk and slowly add to flour mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and cheese.
Combine with macaroni and pour into two 2-quart greased casseroles.
Freeze one for later and bake other at 350° until golden and bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: w. va. skillet cookies
directions: Put butter and dates in a skillet over low heat.
After butter melts, add eggs and sugar.
Stir constantly while cooking for 15 minutes.
When done (it will pull from sides of the pan), remove from heat and mix in Rice Krispies and nuts.
Cool at least 1 hour.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in small amount of margarine.
Mix all ingredients except broth.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan or other casserole.
Add small amount of broth if you like moist dressing. Make gravy from rest of broth.
Cover first half hour.
Uncover last half hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and mix with taco seasoning pack according to directions.
Let cool.
Combine softened cream cheese and taco sauce together; mix well.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt; gradually add scalded milk. Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly (about 10 minutes). Slowly add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture. Cook 5 minutes. Cool. Add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour into baked pie shell and spread with meringue, using the 3 egg whites and your favorite recipe. Sprinkle more coconut on top of meringue. Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice in casserole dish.
Brown pork chops on each side, not done, but brown.
Place on rice.
Cover rice and pork chops with beef consomme and onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. baur's impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend for 30 seconds. (Works just as well in a mixer for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until well mixed.)
Pour into a lightly greased large pie pan or cake pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
There will be a crust on bottom, a
custard in the center and a coconut topping.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and cloves.
Cream until softened butter or margarine.
Add brown sugar gradually until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beaten, until mixed well.
Add gradually while beating molasses and vinegar. Stir in dry ingredients gradually.
Wrap dough in moisture-vaporproof material and chill for 8 hours or overnight. Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Roll one portion of chilled dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut dough with cookie cutters.
Transfer cookies to cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, add decorations with frostings.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen gingerbread men, 2 1/2 dozen round cookies.

title: scallion cheese bread
directions: Made with prebaked pizza crust.

title: chicken stampede
directions: Place all ingredients in covered casserole or roaster pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add grits and bring to a second boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese to grits.
Stir until melted.
Add melted margarine and mix well. Beat eggs.
Add seasonings.
Gradually add eggs to cheese grits mixture.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Cook for 40 minutes.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding mix as directed on package, using 1 cup unsweetened pineapple juice for the liquid instead of the milk. Cool.
When cool, fold in fruit.
Put in a glass serving bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy!

title: miracle soy chicken
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, soy sauce and garlic powder. Put chicken into dish or bowl.

Cover chicken with ingredients and let set several hours in refrigerator. Turn chicken over once in a while. Remove chicken when ready to cook and place on preheated grill. Excellent with potato salad.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Combine pepper, onion and celery (chopped really fine). Mix crabmeat, veggies, dressing and mayonnaise. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni crepes
directions: Beat all ingredients together (batter will be very thin). Ladle onto hot oiled frypan (I use a small Teflon coated frypan). Cook until set; flip over and cook until set.
This recipe makes approximately 22 to 24 crepes.

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 25 minutes at 300°.

title: fresh chopped apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar
and
salad
oil.
Add
vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt
and soda.
Add to mixture and beat well. Stir in apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less if tester comes out clean.

title: chicken breast in wine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
(Pound chicken pieces flat.)
Wrap chicken breasts around a piece of ham and a piece of Swiss cheese. Beat eggs in bowl.
Dip the wrapped chicken breasts in egg and then roll in bread crumbs.
Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Pour white wine into dish.
Do not pour directly onto chicken breasts.
Cover pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 50 minutes, until chicken is firm to the touch.

title: monkey balls
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths, take 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 2/3 cup sugar and shake with biscuits in a bag.
Then put in a greased baking dish.
Heat 1 1/3 cups sugar, 1 1/2 sticks butter, 2 tablespoons cinnamon and vanilla over low heat until smooth (sugar melts).
Pour mixture over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Grease well and dust with flour 2 layer pans or an oblong pan.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed on mixture.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl constantly.
Bake 9-inch layers about 30 minutes, oblong 40 to 50 minutes, or until when touched lightly in center, no imprint remains.
Ice with Fudge Frosting.

title: dian's twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well; do not peel.
Place potatoes in preheated 350° oven and bake whole until halfway done, usually about 30 minutes, depending on size of potatoes.
Take out of oven and let cool.

title: melon thick shake
directions: Freeze cantaloupe cubes on baking sheet.
After frozen, combine strawberries, Karo and vanilla in blender.
Add frozen melon; blend until smooth.
Add yogurt and lemon juice.
Blend until well blended.
Serves 2 large glasses.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add salt, flour and then nuts. Roll into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburg, add diced onions, diced garlic, salt and cut celery, simmer and cover until tender.
Add cut up pepper and cook until tender.
Add can of tomatoes.
Squeeze tomatoes as you add to pan.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add the cooked elbows to the goulash.

title: mint chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine cake mix, egg, whipped topping and peppermint extract. Blend on low speed until thoroughly mixed. Take heaping teaspoonfuls of dough and roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar. Place 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain.
Cool and slice.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan. Saute onion and carrots.
Add cornbread stuffing and mix thoroughly to coat crumbs.
Cover bottom of shallow 2-quart baking dish with this mixture, reserving half for top of casserole.
Add sliced squash, salt and pepper. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over squash. Top with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything together, except cheese.
Cook in microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Put cheese on top and cook 3 more minutes.
Mix in cheese and cook more if necessary.

title: 7-layer peanut butter chip cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian christmas cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Pour into a 2-quart shallow casserole dish or mold, lightly coated with a nonstick vegetable spray. Freeze overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving. You can unmold it onto a serving plate if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Boil first chourico that has been chopped, green split peas, stewed meat and tomatoes for about 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
When all is tender, add 1 cup elbow macaroni.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and 1 1/2 cups water until thick, about 1 minute.
Beat egg yellows and lemon juice.
Add the two together and cook for 5 minutes.
Put into a 9-inch graham crust or baked pie crust.

title: ian's quiche
directions: Add the 1/4 tsp. salt to the flour, then in a large bowl cut the crisco and butter into the flour until it resembles fine breadcrumbs.
Using a knife stir the water into the flour mixture a little at a time until it starts to come together.
Then, using your hand, press the dough together.
It should not be wet or sticky, but should feel soft and not tough.
A good pastry dough should leave the sides of the bowl clean.
Roll out onto a floured board to about 1/4-inch thick, line a 9-inch flan tin, then line with greaseproof paper.
Pour in dried beans or rice, to stop the pastry from rising.
Bake at 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5 for 20 minutes.
When cooked remove the beans from the crust.
